title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown onion, garlic and ground beef.
Drain grease.
Cool. Stir in Mozzarella, crumbs, parsley and egg.
Season to taste. Cook shells in salted water 15 minutes.
Drain.
Stuff.
Spoon layer of sauce in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place shells on sauce, side by side.
Mix wine with remaining sauce.
Pour over shells. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Mix deviled ham and cream cheese together until creamy.
Serve on crackers.
Very good for parties and brunches at work.

title: sand tarts(christmas cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients together and beat into batter until a soft dough forms.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: tomato pie
directions: Prick bottom and sides of pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Coat tomato slices with flour, salt and pepper.
Saute in hot oil until golden brown.
Set aside.

title: earthquake dessert
directions: Cover bottom of pan with coconut.
Cover with nuts (do not stir).
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts (do not stir).
Combine butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon over cake (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan mix together pie filling, pineapple and sugar. Sprinkle cake mix (dry) evenly over top; sprinkle with nuts and dot with oleo.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned scalloped corn
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Mix melted margarine and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs together.
Pour over corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth, then stir in second cup confectioners sugar.
Shape into tiny balls.
Roll each ball in 3/4 cup finely chopped salted peanuts.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate until firm.

title: scallops hawaiian style
directions: Cut scallops into small pieces and salt.
Make a syrup of butter, sugar and pineapple juice.
Dip scallops and pineapple slices in syrup.
Place pineapple in a well greased shallow pan. Put scallops in center of pineapple slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting once with syrup.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve with fruit.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat lemon jello, eggs and water 2 minutes.
Add lemon cake mix and cooking oil.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Ten minutes before cake is done, mix powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Remove cake from oven and place on cooling rack in pan. Use fork and make holes halfway through cake.
Do entire top of cake this way.
Then pour lemon juice mixture on top of cake into the holes and along the edges of the pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Fill 13 x 9-inch baking pan 1/2 full with fruit.
In a large bowl, cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add milk, mixing together. Stir in flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt (if not using self-rising flour).
Mix well and pour over fruit.
In a small bowl, mix 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water; pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: south seas chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in paper bag.
Add chicken, shake to coat.
Reserve 2 Tbsp. flour mixture for gravy. Brown chicken in oil in skillet.
Place chicken in 9x13-inch baking dish.
Add onions, carrots and celery.
Blend reserved flour mixture, brown sugar, and ginger into pan drippings; stir to make smooth paste.
Add orange juice concentrate and 3/4 c water.
Cook until bubbly.
Pour over chicken.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken vegetable bake
directions: Thinly slice chicken.
Flour chicken and saute in olive oil. Season with garlic salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish.
Saute beans, onions and mushrooms in olive oil.
Put on chicken.
Brown flour and margarine.
Mix broth and water and add; mix until blended.
Add garlic, cilantro and red pepper.
Stir in flour to make gravy.
Pour over chicken; cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: big fat cookies
directions: Heat
oven
Grease cookie sheet with shortening. Prepare
the
cake mix as directed on package except use 1/2 cup water
and 2 eggs, omit salad oil.
Drop the dough by rounded tablespoonful
inches
apart
onto
greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake in 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes or until almost no impression remains when a cookie is touched lightly.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute, then lift the
cookies to
rack
with
pancake
turner.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: esther's orange marmalade cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and flour two 9 inch round cake pans; line with wax paper, shaking out excess flour.
In a bowl, sift flour, baking soda, and salt.	In another bowl, beat the butter with an electric mixer until smooth.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, orange zest, and vanilla. Beat in 1/3 of dry ingredients alternately with 1/2 of the buttermilk until combined well.
Add half the remaining dry ingredients and the remaining buttermilk, and beat until combined well.
Finally, beat in the remaining dry ingredients.

title: texas food cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325° and set a rack in the middle level. Butter and flour a 10-inch tube pan.

title: baked yellow squash with fresh tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray or oil (sparsely) a deep 2-quart casserole.
Wash and slice the squash.
Place layer of squash in casserole.
Add layer of tomatoes, then layer of onions.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the herbs, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers and seasonings.
Cover and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat egg, salt and water with beater until foamy.
Add flour while stirring.
Continue to add flour until dough will not stick to sides of bowl.
Roll as thin as possible with rolling pin with plenty of flour.
Cut with pizza cutter.
Let lay until nearly dry.
Have broth nicely seasoned and boiling.
Drop in noodles and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
(Putting noodles in just warm oven for 5 minutes will dry them out nicely.)

title: bacon-fried chicken
directions: Combine milk and egg in a large bowl.
Place chicken pieces in mixture; refrigerate 1 hour.
In a medium size bowl, mix flour, salt, black pepper and cayenne.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour mixture; shake off excess.
Spread bacon over bottom of a large, heavy frying pan.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of bacon in a single layer.
Cook, uncovered, over medium-low heat, turning as chicken browns, for 50 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from the skillet; drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle any loose bacon pieces over chicken before serving.
Serves 8.

title: frosted nuts
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and sour cream.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Add nuts and stir until mixture sugars.
Pour on wax paper.
Separate and let cool thoroughly.
Place in airtight container.
Will keep 3 months.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with beater until well mixed.
Store in chili sauce or salad dressing bottles in refrigerator at least 24 hours before using.
A clove of garlic may be grated and used in place of onion.

title: snicker-doodles
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Mix butter, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend in flour, cream of tarter, baking soda and salt.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Mix 2 Tbsp. of sugar and cinnamon into a bowl.
Roll balls into mixture and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8-10 minutes or until set; immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 5-6 dozen.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Put steak cubes, onion and garlic in crock-pot.
Stir in flour and mix to coat steak cubes.
Add all other ingredients except sour cream.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 10 hours.
Add sour cream 30 minutes before serving and stir in thoroughly.
Serve over hot buttered noodles or rice.
(On high setting, cook 5 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally.)

title: husband's delight casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients and set aside. Brown meat in butter. Add tomato sauce and next 4 ingredients. Cook noodles as directed on package.
In buttered 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of noodles, beef mixture and cream cheese mixture. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: sawmill soup
directions: Peel potatoes, onions and dice.
Place all ingredients in large pot.
Add at least a quart of water.
Cover.
Bring to boil. Lower heat almost to a simmer and cook for 45 minutes and serve.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Add powdered sugar, dry milk, corn syrup, water and vanilla into chocolate.
Stir continuously until well blended and smooth.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Turn into a buttered square pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: joan's dirt cake
directions: Roll cookies to fine crumbs.
Set aside.
Mix pudding and milk.
Chill until thick.
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add Cool Whip and nuts to cheese mixture, then add pudding to this mixture.
Layer cookie crumbs, pudding and cheese mixture in a large glass bowl.
Always start with some cookie crumbs in bottom of bowl and save some to sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate.

title: slop it all together cake
directions: Slop it all together. Mix well. Pour batter into a well-greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato buttermilk soup
directions: Cook onion in oil in medium saucepan until lightly brown.
Stir in flour, then add 2 cups buttermilk.
Stir over low heat until thick.
Add tomatoes and remaining 1 cup buttermilk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Heat, but do not boil.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and baking powder, mixing well, then add milk.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa. Add enough milk to mix sugar and cocoa. Add eggs and beat, then add rest of milk, flavoring and butter. Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush
crackers.
Put
1/2 in bottom of casserole dish. Dot 1/2 of butter on cracker crumbs.
Place chicken on crumbs. Add water
chestnuts.
Mix
soups
and
sour cream.
Pour over top. Add other crumbs and dot with remaining butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients, making sure milk is last.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 350° and continue baking for 40 to 50 minutes more or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool and serve as you would regular pumpkin pie.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix Jell-O in water. Add to cake mix. Add Wesson oil and eggs. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in tube pan.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and rinse off grease.
Return to pan or Dutch oven.
Add water, onion and spices.
Mix well over medium heat.
Add chicken and mushroom soups and enchilada sauce.
Rinse each can with small amount of water and add to pot.
Simmer 10 minutes, mixing well.

title: selah's no guilt banana split
directions: Dissolve Jell-O completely in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Pour into square 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.

title: sam's blackened shrimp
directions: Rinse and drain shrimp. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Corning Ware dish, sprayed with vegetable oil. Place margarine slices on top of shrimp. Pepper shrimp heavily. Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes. Turn shrimp with a spatula. Cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Make crust and place half on bottom of pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and mace together.
Put half of the mixture on bottom and then peaches.
Add rest of sugar mixture on top and put in butter.
Put on top crust.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: glaze for ham
directions: Wash real good.
Put in pan the night before you want to serve them and add water to cover plus 4 more cups water.
Let set and next morning put on stove at low temperature.
Add salt and ham hock (or vegetable oil).
Cook until tender.
Watch and don't let boil dry.
Keep plenty of water in beans.
To add flavor you may put a whole onion in while cooking.

title: economy casserole
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; strain.
Brown ground beef or chuck in skillet; drain off fat.
Add onion, green pepper and one can of mushroom soup with 1/2 can of milk.
Then add cooked macaroni; mix together and add salt and pepper to taste.
"A time saver and also delicious."

title: angel hair pasta
directions: Combine tomatoes, cheese, basil and garlic; set aside.
In a 3-quart saucepan, combine 1 1/3 cups water, milk and margarine; bring just to a boil.
Gradually add pasta while stirring.
Stir in broccoli and boil for 5 to 6 minutes, while stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Add pasta-broccoli mixture to tomato mixture, tossing well.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spiced apple and raisin sauce
directions: In medium skillet, cook apple in margarine until tender.
Stir in brown sugar and cloves.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Stir into apple mixture and cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve warm sauce over turkey.
Makes 2 cups sauce.

title: chuck wagon steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Rub or pound mixture into the meat.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Brown meat well on all sides. Blend beef broth, water, barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add green pepper and olives. Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours longer, until meat is tender. Skim fat from gravy and thicken as desired.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni shells until tender.
Cut crab meat into bite size pieces.
Add chopped onions, celery and eggs.
When shells are done, drain well and let cool.

title: chocolate eggless, butterless, milkless cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl. Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and water.
Mix and beat for 4 minutes. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: lime jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill until partially set. Blend in the mayonnaise.
Fold in all the remaining ingredients. Chill.
Yields 6 to 12 servings.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix well and roll into marble size balls. Place in greased shallow pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or in electric skillet, sear to brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, sour cream, cheese and soup together.
Put mixture in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle cornflakes on top of mixture and drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate krumble bars
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover completely with marshmallows.
Bake 3 minutes.
Cool.

title: scalloped potatoes(from jacket boiled potatoes)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, and pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple-coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add slightly beaten egg yolks and blend well. Add crushed pineapple, including juice. Sift baking powder with flour and add to mixture. Add coconut and vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Allow to cool before frosting.

title: butter-nut pumpkin bars
directions: In a 3-quart mixer bowl, combine margarine, sugar, eggs and pumpkin.
Beat on medium speed, scraping sides of bowl often, until well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Reduce to low speed.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and raisins.

title: potatoes and sausage
directions: Peel potatoes and cut up into small blocks.
Place butter in skillet (with lid) to melt.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper. Smother potatoes until soft.
Slice sausages in small circles and add to potatoes.
Let simmer for 20 minutes on low temperature. Serve with bread.

title: ratatouille
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: creamy jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 3 minutes until completely dissolved. Cool 30 minutes at room temperature. Pour milk into medium bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 minutes. Quickly pour into gelatin. Stir with wire whisk until well blended. Pour into 13 x 9 inch pan. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Dip bottom of pan in warm water about 15 seconds. Cut into decorative shapes with cookie cutters all the way through gelatin or cut into 1 inch squares. Lift pan. Makes about 24 pieces.

title: chunky guacamole
directions: Put avocado flesh into bowl and mash with a fork. Add the remaining ingredients and stir together. Serve with pita or tortilla chips.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in fat in large, heavy skillet.
Add soups, vegetables, dry onion soup mix, sour cream and macaroni. Mix thoroughly.
Turn into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued chuck steak
directions: Trim fat.
Place meat in clear plastic bag.
Place in a deep bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat; close bag. Marinate 2 to 3 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
Turn bag occasionally.
Place meat on grill about 6 inches from heat.
Turn every 10 to 15 minutes.
Grill over medium coals for 35 to 45 minutes (total time for medium rare).
Brush with marinade during last 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings; 291 calories per serving.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook and drain beef.
Add taco seasoning, mix well.
Add diced tomatoes, corn, stir and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour into baking dish.
Prepare Jiffy corn mix according to directions. Pour over top of meat mixture.
Bake at 400 degrees until done.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large pan.
Add onion & saute for 2 minutes.
Add other ingredients & simmer at least 15 minutes.
The longer it simmers, the better it tastes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and 2/3 of Cool Whip. Spread in pie crust and top with remaining Cool Whip. Chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and Crisco together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Cream margarine; add sweetener, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Add flour mixture and stir well.
Mix in chocolate and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.
Carbohydrate 4.8 g, protein 1.0 g, fat 3.2 g, calories 50.
One cookie = 1/4 bread exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: date balls
directions: Put the stick of oleo in a pan over medium heat and then add dates and stir in and remove pan from stove.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Roll the mixture into 1 inch balls, then roll it into a separate bowl with confectioners sugar.

title: spirals and scampi
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, in large skillet, melt butter and oil; saute shrimp, shallots and garlic until almost done.
Add remaining ingredients and continue cooking until shrimp is tender.
Stir in the hot cooked macaroni.
Makes 4 servings.

title: "ole" sarges barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and cook until lemon and onion are mushy.
All water should be boiled out by this time.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add the dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, eggs and banana.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and frost with Sander Buttercream Frosting.

title: picante sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in jars and refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: the bible cake
directions: Mix well and bake in greased and floured pan at 350° until done.
The verses names will tell you what the ingredients are and if followed will give a wonderful result.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Add flour with soda and salt.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in long pan at 350° for 45 minutes or a little longer, if apples are juicy.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: garden rice
directions: Saute green onions, green pepper and squash in 4 tablespoons butter until tender. Add corn, seasonings and parsley. Set aside. Cook rice. Place rice in large bowl. Pour 1/2-cup melted butter over cooked rice and toss lightly. Add seasoned vegetables, tossing again. Place in a buttered casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2). Cover. Heat in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: noodle salad
directions: Mix above ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Set cream cheese out until soft.
Add the rest of the ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Set in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Roll into rolls.
Makes 2.
Then roll in crushed pecans and wrap in Saran Wrap.

title: sesame salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with a spoon (can be put in a shaker).
Do not pour over the salad mixture until just before serving.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Place biscuit mix, rolled oats, sugar, salt and baking powder in large bowl of electric mixer.
Using kitchen shears, snip apricots in thin pieces (or chop fine with knife).
Add apricots and nuts to dry mixture; toss until well coated.
In small bowl of electric mixer, beat the egg.
Add milk; beat until blended. Blend egg-milk mixture with the dry ingredients at medium speed; beat on high speed for 30 seconds.
Turn batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Yields 1 loaf.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In large pot, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid and setting veggies aside.
In a skillet, saute onion in butter until soft. Stir in flour, salt and pepper; gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Gently stir in the cooked veggies. Add 1 cup of more of reserved cooking liquid until soup is the desired consistency.
Yields 8 to 10 servings (about 2 1/2 quarts).

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Prepare 1/2 recipe of "Deluxe Rolls".
When dough is light, turn out on board and roll into a rectangle 1/4-inch thick and about 8-inches wide.
Brush with melted butter.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large pot.
Add water and bouillon. Bring to a boil and add broccoli and egg noodles.
Cook 20 minutes.
Then add cheese and melt.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: old fashioned cheese potatoes
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until a thick paste forms.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Add cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted.
Place potatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake uncovered at 350° about 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Good and easy!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and core apples; coarsely chop and measure 1 3/4 cups into large bowl.
Add sugar; let stand 10 minutes.
Sift flour; measure.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Sift again.
Blend melted butter and egg into apple mixture.
Add flour, stirring until just blended.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Pour into greased pan (8-inch square).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: miso beer chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients; soak overnight.
Cook on hibachi.

title: cereal bars
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and peanut butter together until sugar melts.
Pour over cereal.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 13 pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Pour over the top.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box; drain.
In greased casserole dish, arrange layer of macaroni.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put pats of margarine in corners of casserole. Sprinkle layer with Parmesan cheese.
Next, add layer of tomatoes, broken in pieces.
Cover with layer of shredded sharp cheese. Sprinkle layer with bread crumbs.
Repeat process, starting with macaroni again and ending with bread crumbs, until ingredients are finished.
Pour juice from tomatoes in corners of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil syrup, sugar, cream of tartar and vinegar to soft ball stage.
Add butter and baking soda.
Pour over freshly popped corn; cool and shape into 15 balls.

title: crustless salmon quiche(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch baking dish or pie plate with nonstick spray.
Set aside.

title: easy pie(chocolate)
directions: Melt Hershey bars.
Mix in Cool Whip.
While chocolate is still hot, pour into graham crust and chill.
This is rich, but good.

title: finger-lickin' chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate in refrigerator 3 or 4 days. Turn the plastic bag every day, or turn the chicken wings in the marinade.
Bake, uncovered, in shallow baking pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot peppered steak
directions: Put meat in crock-pot and stir in flour; add peppers, onions, salt, pepper, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cook four hours on high or 7 hours on low.

title: apricot fritters
directions: Dry apricot halves on paper toweling until as dry as possible. Beat egg with milk; stir in the melted Crisco.
Combine the flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture and stir just until mixed.
Dip apricots in batter.
Fry a few at a time in Crisco heated to 365° until fritters are brown, about 4 minutes, turning once.
(Do not use the frying basket.) Drain on paper toweling.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Serve warm.

title: orange no-bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut in a large bowl.
(Best to mix by hand.)
Shape dough into teaspoon size balls and roll in coconut.

title: cherry cake
directions: Follow directions on box except reduce water to 1/2 cup.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and top with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: timmie's famous cookies
directions: Mix together.
Spoon onto foil covered sheet.
Bake at 325°. Time depends on size.
Let cool 3 to 4 minutes before removing from foil.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Melt butter in hot milk.
Add flour and baking powder to egg mixture and fold while adding milk with melted butter.
Pour into ungreased pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 275° oven for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the butter with melted chocolate.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add vanilla and salt.
Fold in flour and chopped pecans.
Bake in shallow 12 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked grits
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Gradually stir grits into briskly boiling salted water.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook grits for 15 or 20 minutes or until grits are thick.
Stir often while cooking.
Add butter, cheese, milk and eggs.
Stir grits until butter and cheese are melted.
Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peach chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
In double boiler, combine remaining ingredients.
Cook over boiling water until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons cornstarch to gelatin in water and mix until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff; add 1/2 cup sugar. Fold gelatin mixture into egg whites.
Pour into baked pastry shell; chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt together.
Let stand 3 hours.
Mix

title: persimmon cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add pulp; beat.
Add all dry ingredients (except soda) sifted together.
Add soda, dissolved in warm water, and lemon juice.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: cashew tuna casserole
directions: Blend soup with water.
Combine all other ingredients.
(Save a few noodles for top.)
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: sue ashworth's liver, liver
directions: Soak liver in hot water.
Fry bacon and reserve drippings to brown liver in.
Remove liver from hot water and sprinkle with m.s.g.
Roll in flour and brown in bacon drippings.
Slice onion and bring to boil in the water.
Remove liver from skillet.
Add 2/3 tablespoon flour, salt and pepper and brown as to make gravy. Use the water from the onions to make gravy.
Put liver and onions in the gravy and cover; cook on low heat about 30 minutes until very tender.

title: apple pie
directions: Open can of apples and spread them in a square or round pan. Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg on apples, as much as desired.
Melt margarine on the stove in a pot.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour and sugar with a fork.
Ingredients in pot should be crumbly.
With a fork, put crumbs over apples all over top, then sprinkle more cinnamon.
Put in oven on 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pork sausage ring
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into ring in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Fill center with scrambled eggs, if desired.
Garnish with parsley and crabapples.
Serves 12.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Do not overmix.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup chopped nuts. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash pickles
directions: Make a brine of salt and water.
Put in squash, onions and peppers.
Let stand for 1 to 2 hours.
Drain, rinse and drain well.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, melted margarine and powdered sugar together.
Make into balls.

title: great balls 'o' fire
directions: Combine the first six ingredients; mix well and shape into one-inch balls.
Brown meatballs in a large skillet with hot oil until lightly browned; drain meatballs in a colander sitting on a dish and discard drippings.
Combine chili sauce and grape jelly in skillet; cook over medium heat until jelly has melted.
Stir occasionally to keep from burning or sticking.
Add meatballs and simmer for 10 to 20 minutes; transfer sauce and meatballs to a crock-pot or chafing dish to keep warm.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup of liquid.
Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1 cup hot water. Add juice mixture to gelatin mixture.
Add lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add fruit and nuts.
Chill in a 5-cup mold overnight.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, 1 tablespoon sugar and vanilla.
Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch, water, orange juice, lemon juice and salt.
Cook over medium heat, bring to boil for 1 minute.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. (Hint: Can pour boiling water over dried beef, let stand a minute then drain. This tones down the salt in the dried beef.) Let set in fridge for at least an hour. Cube rye bread and dip in mixture.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well; cut in butter with a pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead lightly 8 to 10 times.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: frozen cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze. Will keep indefinitely.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving so it will be slushy. Makes fifteen 1/2-cup servings.

title: gerald chili
directions: Cook hamburger meat until brown.
Drain off grease.
Stir in all ingredients in a separate pot.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Crush cookies in blender, reserving 1/8 cup.
Melt butter; pour over cookies.
Mix well.
Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill between layers.
Whip together cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Fold in 1/2 the Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Prepare pudding with milk; spread over cream cheese mixture. Chill 3 to 5 minutes until firm.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and add alternately with buttermilk plus soda.

title: butter
directions: Pour cream in a jar; cover top with plastic wrap and seal with the lid.
Sit in the floor and shake, shake, shake.
Pass the jar when tired!
Discuss the changes you see as you shake!
The butter will form a mass separate from the skim milk.
Pour contents into colander; drain.
Place butter on plate.
Add salt, if wanted, and enjoy!

title: mincemeat
directions: Note:
Apples should be 2 to 1 mixture with meat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In small deep pan, spread cooked Stove Top stuffing.
Spread chicken chunks and add cheese on top.
Mix eggs and milk; pour on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not cover.

title: orange-cranberry bread
directions: Mix cranberries with 1/4 cup of the sugar and put aside.
Put orange through the food chopper.
Put juice and rind in measuring cup and fill with boiling water to make 1 cup.
Add the butter, egg and sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Fold in nuts and cranberries; pour batter into a well-greased pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool on rack.

title: round steak and rice
directions: Melt oleo; add steak, onions, carrots and seasonings.
Cook until meat is tender.
Cook rice.
Add to meat mixture.

title: peach-nectar punch
directions: Drain peaches; reserve syrup.
Stud peaches with cloves. Place peaches and cinnamon sticks in bottom of ring mold.
Fill with apple juice (3 cups) and freeze.
In punch bowl, combine peach syrup and remaining ingredients.
Float ice ring.
Makes 14 cups.

title: shrimp spread appetizer
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Rinse meat under cold running water and pat dry with paper towels.
Put garlic cloves, oregano, peppercorns and salt in a mortar.
Pound with a pestel until crushed.
Add olive oil and vinegar; mix thoroughly.
Rub seasoning into the steaks.
Dip each slice in the eggs, then coat with bread crumbs, pressing crumbs into both sides with heel of hand.
Heat oil in
a large skillet, frying pan or deep fryer and fry until golden brown (about 4 to 5 minutes, depending upon thickness).
Drain on absorbent paper towels.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Prepare the night before:
Layer bread, 2 slices deep in
a buttered 9 x 13 baking dish.
Beat eggs with next 5 ingredients. Pour over bread and dot with butter.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake until done in a greased jelly roll pan (11 x 16-inch); set aside.
Blend instant pudding with milk, then blend in cream cheese and Cool Whip.
When cake is cool, spread this mixture over it.
Next, top with the pineapple, then the coconut and, finally, the nuts.
Serve at once, or put into fridge until ready to serve.

title: spinach and orange salad
directions: Combine above ingredients in blender or food processor. Refrigerate to chill and combine flavors.

title: danish potato soup
directions: In a soup kettle, bring ham bone and 2 quarts water to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until meat pulls away from the bone.
Remove ham bone.
When cool enough to handle, trim any meat and dice.
Discard bone.
Return ham to kettle along with potatoes, onions, celery, parsley, cabbage and carrots; cook 40 minutes.
Stir together flour and 1/4 cup cold water.
Slowly pour into the soup, stirring constantly.
Bring soup to a boil; cook 2 minutes.
Reduce heat; stir in cream.
Remove from the heat. Sprinkle a dash of nutmeg on each bowlful just before serving.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar and evaporated milk in heavy saucepan. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer 6 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat and add chocolate, stirring until blended. Add butter and vanilla and stir. Refrigerate until mixture begins to thicken, about 30 minutes. Beat chocolate mixture until thick and creamy. Fold into whipped cream. Chill until spreadable. Makes 3 1/3 cups, enough to frost one 2 layer cake.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Let sherbet soften for 15 minutes.
Scoop into punch bowl and pour cold ginger ale over it.

title: cheese tempters
directions: Combine cheese and butter until well blended.
Add flour and mix.
Add cereal and mix until mixture holds together.
Pinch off 2 teaspoons and roll into balls.
Sprinkle with paprika and place balls on ungreased baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 25.

title: cinnamon oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray baking sheet lightly with vegetable cooking spray.
Mix sugar, margarine, egg substitute, vanilla and cinnamon.
Blend in oats, then add no fat biscuit mix. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto plate with cinnamon/sugar mix; roll dough balls in cinnamon/sugar mix.
Place dough balls on prepared pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old-fashioned turkey pot pies
directions: Mix turkey, mixed vegetables and seasonings.
Put in pie crust and cover with pie crust.
Slit with knife. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked hominy
directions: Boil hominy, chilies and butter together until almost all liquid is gone.
Add cheese and sour cream.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° until heated through.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Let margarine and cheese come to room temperature until very soft and fluffy.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into tiny balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Don't let them get too brown.
Makes 90 wafers.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: This is my Mom's recipe.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add pineapple, lemon juice & mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip, and put into pie crusts and chill.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate. Serve with fajitas, chips, egg dishes.

title: lemon glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat hard to blend.
Drizzle over top of cake.
This icing adds flavor and helps to retain moisture.

title: potato magics
directions: Place quartered potatoes in a large saucepan; add water to cover.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain water, mash potatoes and allow to cool.
Saute chopped onions in olive oil until clear.
Add onions, cracker or bread crumbs, salt and pepper to potatoes and remash them.
Coat a cookie sheet with a nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Roll mixture into balls with your hands and place the balls on the cookie sheet.
Brush them with beaten egg yolks.
Bake until crusty brown, about 45 minutes in a 400° oven.
Serve as appetizer side dish, snack or even with brunch.
Yield:
about 24 large or 72 small puffs.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, spread 1 cup sour cream.
In 2-quart saucepan with fork, flake chicken; add 1/2 cup sour cream, mushrooms and next 6 ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until heated.
In 8-inch skillet over medium heat in 1/2-inch hot oil, fry 1 tortilla a few seconds on each side until soft.
Along center of tortilla, spread 1/4 cup chicken mixture; fold and place seam side down, in sour cream pan.
Repeat. Preheat oven to 450°.
Spread enchiladas with remaining sour cream, then top with cheese.
Bake 8 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with juice from fruit.
Last add fruit, pecans and raisins.
Bake in one 10-inch tube pan or two loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove stem ends, seeds and membrane.
Cook for 5 minutes in 1 cup salty boiling water.
Drain; brown beef and onion, stirring with fork.
Add other ingredients (except bread crumbs).
Mix well.
Fill peppers with meat mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.

title: dreamsicle
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Add an amount of crushed ice to fill blender.
Use high button.
Serve in frosty glasses!

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer 1 can of asparagus, 3 sliced hard-boiled eggs and 1/2 can of cream of mushroom soup. Do that twice. Crumble 6 to 8 Ritz crackers for a top layer. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: soup-in-a-hurry
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer.

title: "minuteman macaroons"
directions: Combine the ingredients, mix well!
Drop from a teaspoon 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or lightly browned.
Remove at once or they will stick. Makes about 30.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Cook the fruit and water for 3 minutes. Cool.
Add balance of ingredients.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Mix with spices, cook 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Rinse with cold water.
Grease large 13 x 9-inch pan.
Alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce and cheese, ending with noodles.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: confederate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line baking sheet (14 x 16-inch) with aluminum foil.
Place graham crackers tightly on sheet pan.
Melt butter and oleo.
Add sugar; boil for 3 minutes, constantly stirring.
Pour over crackers and spread.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over that.
Bake for 10 minutes on middle rack.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes, then break apart.
Good, good.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves. Stir in whipping cream and half and half.
Pour mixture into freezer container of a 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Pack freezer with additional ice and rock salt and let stand 1 hour before serving.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: imitation condensed milk
directions: Mix equal amounts ginger ale and white grape juice.
Chill and serve.
To make an ice ring for the punch, pour punch mixture into a ring mold adding drained cherries and/or grapes.
To get ice ring out of mold, quickly dip mold into pan of warm water and invert onto a plate.
Slowly slide ice ring into punch bowl and fill with punch.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice and wash cucumbers; chop onions and peppers.
Soak cucumbers, peppers, onions and salt on ice for 3 hours, then drain. Add vinegar, sugar and spices (not cucumbers); let come to a rolling boil.
Pour on cucumbers and put back on burner and heat (not boil).
Put in jars.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients together well.

title: one bowl buttercream frosting(no cooking)
directions: Cream butter or margarine in small mixing bowl.
Add cocoa and confectioners sugar alternately with milk; beat to spreading consistency (additional tablespoon milk may be needed).
Blend in vanilla.
Yields about 2 cups frosting.

title: meatball soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water in 4-quart saucepan.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder.
Simmer over low heat.
Mix meat, rice, salt, pepper and egg lightly, but thoroughly.
Shape into 60 small meatballs, 1 rounded teaspoonful of meat mixture for each ball. Saute onion in oil in frying pan until tender.
Remove.
Add to soup.
Lightly brown meatballs in pan; drain excess fat.
Drop into boiling soup.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: luscious cheese cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let set 20 minutes.
Mix together sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla and spread on top of warm cake.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: (dry) russian tea
directions: Mix
all
together.
Store
in a tight jar or container. Use 2 teaspoons into 1 cup boiling water.
Stir and enjoy.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer chicken on bottom of pan.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Layer over chicken.
Place cracker crumbs on top of soup layer.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Pour melted margarine over the entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butter frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk together.
Cook until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Cream together butter and shortening.
Beat 4 minutes.
Add sugar.
Beat 4 more minutes.
Add the paste mixture with vanilla and, once again, beat 4 minutes.

title: date squares
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: salsa fria
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve very cold. Serve with hot barbecued steaks or hamburgers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: quick bean soup
directions: Simmer sausage in small amount of water, then slice.
To water left in pan, add all other ingredients and simmer until flavors are cooked through.

title: damn good chili
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper. Add remaining ingredients except beans. Simmer 1/2 hour. Add beans.
Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Increase cayenne or chili powder for hotter chili.

title: jello salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar, stirring constantly for 5 minutes. Dissolve jello in hot water. Combine with pineapple.
Refrigerate until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in sour cream, pecans and cheese.
Mold and chill before serving.

title: mom's fancy fried apples(canning)
directions: Using several different types of apples is best:
Cortland, McIntosh, and Franklin at one time; Yellow Delicious and Melrose at another.
Mix different types of apples as you go, or mix in skillet.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Cream bananas until fluffy.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with the dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread-and-butter pudding
directions: In a
buttered oval gratin dish, sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the golden
raisins and currants.
Arrange sliced bread to cover the dish
and
drizzle melted butter over it.
In a bowl with an electric
mixer, beat eggs and egg yolk until they are combined; add 1/4
cup sugar a little at a time, and beat the mixture until it ribbons.
Whisk in the heavy cream and strain the mixture
over the bread.
Sprinkle with remaining raisins and currants.
Set the
gratin
dish in a baking pan and pour enough hot water into the pan to reach halfway up the sides of the dish.
Bake
at 300° for 1 hour.
Remove the dish from the pan, sprinkle
the pudding with 1 tablespoon sugar and put the dish under a
preheated broiler
for 1 to 2 minutes, or until the top
is golden brown and the sugar is caramelized.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pickled sausage slices
directions: In saucepan, bring water, vinegar, sugar, pickling spices, salt and allspice to boil; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Set aside.

title: microwave swiss steak
directions: Trim steak and pound well.
Cut into 6 to 8 pieces.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat beef with flour mixture.
Place meat and remaining flour mixture into rectangular baking dish, 12 x 8-inch or 10-inch square.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix the sugar and whipping cream thoroughly and place in microwave for 12 minutes on high setting. Remove from microwave and add the rest of ingredients. Stir until the mixture begins to get firm. Drop from spoon onto wax paper and let cool. (Delicious and only takes 15 minutes.)

title: dirty rice
directions: Put ground meat into skillet.
Add a little steak seasoning and a little red pepper and start cooking.
While ground meat is frying, cut up onion, bell pepper and green onions into small pieces.
Drain grease from meat when halfway cooked.
Add bell pepper, onion and green onions.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Add more steak seasoning and red pepper, if needed.
When meat, bell pepper and onions are fully cooked, add 2 1/3 cups water per box.
Stir in contents of both boxes.
(Use only 1 Uncle Ben's seasoning packet.)
Cover tightly and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 25 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all together. Serve with sliced apples.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water; let cool.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
After this is firm, mix next 4 ingredients.
Spread over gelatin mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over this.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, margarine and 3 cups milk in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Blend eggs, salt and remaining milk.
Add to cornmeal mixture.
Mix well. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: salmon log
directions: Add salmon juice to gelatin.
Flake salmon.
Mix with onion, cream cheese and gelatin.
Shape like a log and chill.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer as listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes two layers of each.
Top with boiled eggs and imitation bacon chips.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make biscuit dough from first 5 ingredients.
Roll out into an oblong 1/3 to 1/2 inch thick.
Cover with grated apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up as for cinnamon rolls, then slice 1 inch thick.
Place cut side up in buttered 13 x 15-inch baking dish.
Dot each with a dab of butter.
Bring sugar and water to boil; remove from heat.
Pour syrup over all.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until biscuits have browned and syrup bubbles.

title: george washington cherry bisque
directions: Beat egg whites foamy.
Add sugar gradually and beat until stiff.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle more Grape Nuts in bottom of cup cake liners placed in the muffin pans.
Pour more Grape Nuts on top and freeze.

title: quinoa tabouleh
directions: Put the quinoa in a wire strainer and thoroughly rinse with hot water to remove any bitter flavor.

title: sweet tomato relish
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water, slip off skins.
Cut out core and cut into 4 pieces.
Put tomatoes in boiler, mash a little to get some juices.
Cook until they are mushy.
Stir every once in a while.

title: glorified chicken
directions: Skillet: In skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes, or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat. Stir in soup, pepper and thyme.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 35 minutes, or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add orange juice, butter and boiling water.
Stir well.
Add egg, cranberries and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry lemon freeze
directions: Combine in blender the strawberries, juice, lemonade, sugar and ice.
Blend until slushy.
Serve immediately.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in pear liquid; add the hot mixture to cream cheese.
Stir until smoothly blended on low speed of mixer.
Cool and let set slightly.
Add large can diced pears, chopped nuts and coconut.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with a cherry.

title: double chili cheese dip
directions: Serve with cocktail rye bread.
Serves 6.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook sausage;
add
onion and bell pepper.
Add to your favorite meat sauce.
In
large
baking
dish layer spaghetti, sauce, cheese and pepperoni alternately, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.	This keeps well.

title: my cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Season to taste with the following:
salt, pepper, red pepper, lemon juice, sugar, Italian seasoning, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, onion salt, oregano, celery salt, chili powder, garlic salt, cumin and lemon pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook broccoli.
Add broccoli to other ingredients.
Put in a buttered baking dish. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
May put grated cheese while still hot.
You may add 1 small can chopped green chilies for a little extra snap.

title: layered chicken salad
directions: Layer 1 1/2 c. chicken and lettuce in a 3 qt. bowl.
Combine rice, peas, parsley; spoon evenly over lettuce.
Layer tomatoes, cucumber, pepper and remaining 1 1/2 c. chicken.
Spoon dressing evenly over top of salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Top with pepper rings; cover and chill 8 hours.
Toss before serving.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in bowl; mix well.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla and butter; mix well.
Stir in corn.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until pudding is set.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: fruit spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, cantaloupe balls and strawberries in a large salad bowl; toss gently. Combine jam and next 3 ingredients in a small bowl; stir with a wire whisk or shake in a covered jar. Drizzle over spinach mixture and toss well. Makes 6 servings. Each has 70 calories and 1.9 g fat.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine and oil, stirring constantly until tender.
Dissolve 6 cubes in boiling water and gradually add to onions.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Bring to full boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve with Jack cheese and French bread.
Makes 8 servings.

title: southwest breakfast burrito
directions: Separate eggs.
Then scramble them.
Add salsa, grated cheese and then the milk.
Mix together.
Start cooking sausage in a skillet.
Start cooking the mixture of eggs.
Cook sausage until brown.
Wait for eggs to have no juice and they are fluffy.
Warm tortilla, place eggs in middle, then put sausage on top of eggs. Fold tortilla around eggs and sausage.
Add ketchup, salsa or topping of your choice.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a large pan, mix ingredients together, placing chicken breasts on top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: tuna wiggle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles in boiling water until done, about 8 minutes.
Drain noodles and put in 1-quart baking dish.
Drain tuna and add to noodles, add soup and milk and mix. Stir in chopped water chestnuts and chopped celery if used. Sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake until hot throughout, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chips and oleo.
Cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows. Divide mixture in half and form 2 large rolls.
Roll each in coconut.
Wrap rolls in wax paper and chill for 24 hours.
When ready to use, slice into 1/2-inch cookies.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: In a small pan, heat water and bouillon cube to boiling.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Cook 5 minutes; remove from heat but do not drain.
In a large pot, melt butter and slowly stir in the flour. Gradually add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in cheese, soup, onion, sauce and pepper.
Add the broccoli and cheese mixture.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine olive oil, minced garlic, onion and green pepper in Dutch oven or large pot.
Saute until tender.
Add pork and brown. Add tomato puree and tomato paste, stirring until combined. Strain whole tomatoes through strainer (mash by hand) so that only the juice goes into the sauce.
Add remaining ingredients and season to taste.
Simmer over very low heat for 1 hour, stirring constantly.
Sauce freezes well and recipe makes plenty!

title: black bean soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Place onions and celery in 3-quart casserole.
In blender, whirl 1 can beans and 1 cup bouillon, then do the same with the second can of beans and another cup of bouillon.
When smooth, add to casserole with remaining 2 cups bouillon, bay leaf, mustard, parsley and turkey. Stir well.
Bake until beans are tender, approximately 40 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Add sherry and stir well.
Serves 4.

title: beef brisket
directions: Rub dry ingredients into brisket and let stand 1 hour.
Rub in liquid smoke and wrap in foil; place in roaster and let stand overnight.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.

title: marinated green beans and shrimp
directions: Wash and drain beans.
Boil shrimp with shrimp boil and peel. Boil together sugar, salt, cider and cooking oil.
Layer beans, onion and shrimp.
Pour hot mixture over beans, onion and shrimp. Put 2 cloves garlic on toothpicks in beans.
Remove garlic before serving.
Marinate for 24 hours.
Use a deep bowl to make layers.

title: potato pork chop bake
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Line 2 1/2-quart casserole with potatoes.
Mix onion, soup, milk, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Pour over potatoes.
Put chops on top of sauce.
Cover. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done in a 350° oven.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and corn.
Season with salt, pepper and chili powder. Add noodles.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle with chili powder and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Place each chicken breast on a sheet of waxed paper.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or pound with rolling pin.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into egg mixture and then dip each in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken in hot oil in a large skillet; drain on paper towels.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Drain oil from skillet.
Combine tomato sauce, basil, oregano and garlic powder in skillet.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in butter.
Pour mixture over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes. Uncover and arrange Mozzarella cheese slices on top.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: grilled vegetable kabobs
directions: On 6 skewers, alternately thread vegetables, separating onion layers.
Brush on all sides with oil and sprinkle with garlic and seasoned salts.
Broil on rack in broiler pan about 5 minutes on each side or grill on barbecue grill for 7 to 10 minutes on each side.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Let set for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut into rectangles and serve.
May be made ahead and frozen.
This makes a nice casserole if poured into a buttered glass baking dish and baked at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until brown and firm.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix Crisco, egg and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Then add the 2 cups grated apple and mix.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch tin for 30 minutes.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine eggs and milk; stir in bread crumbs, onions, parsley, sage and pepper.
Add ground beef.
Thoroughly mix meat and seasonings.
Spoon meat mixture in loaf pan.
Bake mixture in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cabbage potato saute(for a restricted diet)
directions: In a saucepan, cook cabbage in water until tender.
Stir occasionally; drain.
Add potato, margarine, salt and pepper. Stir in vinegar.
Cook and stir over low heat for 5 minutes. Yield:
4 servings.

title: laplander frosting chocolate
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add other ingredients, then cook in saucepan on high until mixture boils, stirring all the time. Remove from heat, then pour into electric mixer bowl or beat with spoon.
Beat the mixture until cold and thick enough to spread. This you must watch carefully and stir constantly while cooking, for it burns easily.
For a large cake, double the recipe.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese and flour; mix in margarine.
Work dough with hands if it seems dry.
Mold approximately 1 teaspoonful of dough around each olive, shaping into a ball.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine.
Chill 16 to 24 hours.
Will keep for a week in refrigerator.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix with ingredients as instructed on box. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender.
Set aside.
Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Add to butter mixture.
Place Cool Whip lid in bottom of an 8-inch plastic flowerpot.
Layer crushed cookies, then cream/pudding mixture, continuing to layer, finishing with layer of cookies on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with artificial flowers and use dirt scoop to serve the cake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.

title: grandma's peach crumble
directions: Combine peaches and brown sugar in an 8 x 8-inch square pan. In a bowl, mix together the remaining ingredients and sprinkle over the top of peach mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve with ice cream.

title: never fail marshmallow fudge
directions: Put chocolate chips, dark unsweetened chocolate, nuts, marshmallow cream and vanilla in large bowl.
Put remaining ingredients into saucepan; bring to boil.
Boil rapidly for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture into bowl of chocolate mixture.
Stir with heavy spoon until all melted.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables in water and seasoned salt until tender-crisp, uncovered.
Drain vegetables and mix with soup.
Combine stuffing, spices and melted butter.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be made early and refrigerated.

title: cheesy potato snacks
directions: Place cottage fries on a large cookie sheet.
Prepare as directed on package.
Top each cottage fry with cheese.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
Garnish with olives and pepper. Serve hot.
Makes 4 dozen.
Preparation time is 20 minutes.

title: black bottom cupcakes(40 cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9-inch spring-form pan. Combine chocolate crumbs, melted butter and cinnamon in large bowl. Press into bottom of prepared pan.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer and blend well. Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add creme de menthe, peppermint and salt.
Beat again.
Pour mixture into prepared crust.
Add chocolate chips and stir very gently.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°. Turn off heat and let cake cool in oven with door closed 1 hour. Refrigerate cheese cake in pan until ready to serve.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Place sugar and flour in large bowl.
Bring margarine, Crisco, cocoa and water to a rapid boil.
Pour this slowly over the flour and sugar mixture, beating well.
Add buttermilk and soda mix, then add eggs.
Mix, then add cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes (bake at 375° if glass pan is used).

title: instant pie
directions: Mix pudding and half and half until well blended. Stir in ice cream well. Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip when served.

title: double chocolate bars
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts and mix well.
Melt the margarine in a large bowl in the microwave (or on top of stove); add sugar.
Cool slightly and add beaten eggs and vanilla.
To the margarine and sugar mixture, add flour mix a small amount at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Turn dough out into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle chocolate pieces over top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool in pan and cut into bars. Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Place lettuce or spinach and onions in a large salad bowl. Sprinkle with pepper; set aside.
In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Do not drain off drippings. Stir in vinegar, lemon juice, sugar and salt. Pour over lettuce and toss gently until well coated.
Top with hard-cooked egg. Serve immediately. Yield: 6 servings.

title: soy starter or base
directions: Blend or stir all ingredients until smooth.
Cook in an uncovered dish at 350° for 50 minutes (stir after 20 minutes).
Soy starter will keep in refrigerator for a few days or may be frozen. Freeze in 1/2 or 1-cup proportion in plastic freezer bags.
May be used for making soy milk, mayonnaise, yogurt, etc.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into hot, greased, iron skillet and bake until done at 350°.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream
sugar, shortening and eggs thoroughly.
Add milk and vanilla
to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon flour into dry measuring
cup.
Level
off
and pour measured flour onto waxed paper.
Add soda to flour.	Stir to blend.	Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.	Stir in potato chips and
nuts.	Drop
by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake
at
for
10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen cookies.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni noodles; drain.
Brown hamburger with onion. Add salt and pepper.
Combine hamburger and macaroni.
Add pizza sauce, tomato paste, tomato sauce and sugar; mix together.
Add garlic salt, onion salt and oregano.
Place 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Add remaining mixture; top with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom delights
directions: Cream 1 stick oleo with 9 ounces cream cheese.	Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour to make soft dough.
Roll in wax paper and chill 1 hour. Chop mushrooms and onion finely.
Saute in 3 tablespoons oleo 5 minutes.
Blend in 2 tablespoons flour, 1 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper and 1/4 teaspoon thyme.
Stir in 1/4 cup sour cream.
Remove from heat.	Roll dough out thinly.	Pat in mini-muffin pan and bake at 450° about 12 minutes.
Fill with mushroom mixture.
Good hot or cold.

title: maine blueberry muffins
directions: Shake blueberries in a little flour.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Mix milk and egg and add to flour mixture.
Add blueberries.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients except cinnamon and sugar mixture and bake in muffin tins in oven (400°) for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Return to oven and brown.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Place turkey in a large skillet and season. Heat with a small amount of water. Add soup and broth, stirring well until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Stir in cooked spaghetti.
Turn into a 9 x 13 baking dish. Top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sweet rye bread(sott rug brod)
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
In a large bowl mix sugar, molasses, shortening, salt, caraway seed and anise.
Mix in hot water and set aside until lukewarm.
Then blend in 1 cup flour, beating until smooth.
Stir softened yeast and add, mixing well.
Add rye flour and beat until very smooth.
Then beat in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn it onto a very lightly floured surface.
Allow dough to rest 5 to 10 minutes.
Knead.
Form dough into a large ball and put into a greased, deep bowl.
Turn to bring greased surface on top.
Cover with waxed paper and a towel and let stand in warm place (about 80°) until double in volume.
Punch down with fist; pull edges into center and turn dough completely over in bowl.
Cover and let rise again until dough is nearly doubled.
Punch down dough and turn out on a lightly floured surface.
Grease the baking sheet. Divide dough into 2 portions and shape into balls.
Cover and allow to rest 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove to greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise until dough is doubled.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: curry-chicken broccoli
directions: Press cooked broccoli firmly in bottom of dish.
Top with chicken slices.
Combine everything else in large bowl (except butter and bread crumbs).
Pour over chicken slices.
Melt butter and add to bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken cheddar puffs
directions: Melt butter in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add flour and a dash of salt.
Stir vigorously.
Cook and stir until the mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Cool slightly, then add egg and beat vigorously, until smooth.
Stir in cheese.
Drop dough on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool and fill with chicken salad.

title: brownies
directions: Add cocoa to melted shortening.
Beat eggs; add to chocolate mixture.
Sift together the sugar, flour, baking powder and salt. Add dry ingredients to chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine undiluted soup, mayonnaise, onion and eggs.
Stir into broccoli.
Put into large ungreased casserole; sprinkle cheese on top.
Stir stuffing in melted oleo. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can also be put in small dishes and frozen before baking.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend beaten egg yolks, milk and 1/2 cup sugar. Slowly add lime juice.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In large bowl, combine ground meat, eggs, crackers, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well; shape into meatballs.
Brown meatballs in skillet until no pink color remains. Drain well on paper towel. Combine cranberry sauce and tomato soup.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Pour over meatballs.
Heat in oven for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix
together
the
spice cake mix, raisins, oil, applesauce and egg.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Drop from a teaspoon onto
an ungreased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: stir me nots
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour melted butter into 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly over melted butter.
Do the same with coconut.
Now do the same with chocolate bits.
Pour condensed milk evenly over all.
Top with chopped walnuts. Do not stir.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
(Only use sweetened condensed milk, do not substitute with something else.)

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Arrange in buttered dish.
Layer chicken.
In separate dish, combine soup, milk, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken, sprinkle cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: california bundt cake
directions: Mix dry
ingredients
well.
Add bananas, oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple with juice.
Stir to blend well, but do not beat. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for
an
hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool
in
pan
on rack completely before removing cake from pan.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Blend flour and sugar.
Add butter and egg.
Fold in vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips; mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cranberry gelatin mold
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add orange and process 30 seconds or until chopped.
Add cranberries and process 1 minute.
Combine cranberry mixture and sugar in a bowl; let stand 15 minutes or until sugar dissolves.
Sprinkle unflavored gelatin over cold water in a bowl.
Stir and let stand 1 minute. Add lemon flavored gelatin and boiling water; stir 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir cranberry mixture into gelatin mixture.

title: fat-be-gone party casserole potatoes
directions: Beat sour cream and cream cheese together in mixing bowl until smooth.
Gradually add to mashed potatoes, beat until until fluffy and light.
Add parsley flakes, chives and garlic salt to taste. Mix well.
Spray a baking dish with cooking spray.
Add potato mixture.
Brush top with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika. Top with cheese after 20 minutes and bake another 10 minutes in 350° oven.
May be frozen up to 10 days before baking.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar in large bowl.
Add egg; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: richics
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and sift with soda. Combine with brown sugar. Beat eggs well. Add nuts, then flour mixture.
Mix well and add vanilla and melted margarine. Spread in well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut in 1 1/2 x 1-inch strips.

title: pina colada flip
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients in punch bowl, mixing well. Spoon in ice cream.
Add club soda slowly.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into egg.
Coat with bread crumbs.
In a skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Cook chicken 10 minutes or until done.
Set chicken aside.
In the same pan, heat spaghetti sauce to a boil.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Top chicken with cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with spaghetti and additional sauce, if necessary.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti, set aside.
Dice the onion, pepper and tomato.
Mix the ingredients together.
Add the Salad Supreme and dressing.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container. To make, stir 2 to 3 teaspoons into a cup of boiling water. Add orange slice.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Grease large casserole or 2 small ones.
Put chicken, cheese and onion in each tortilla and fold over.
Place in casserole. Blend Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth.
Pour over casserole and bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place yeast in water.
Melt butter and add sugar and egg.
Add yeast, then flour.
The batter will be thin and requires no kneading.
Put in airtight bowl and refrigerate.
Bake in muffin pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Boil potatoes and drain.
Add butter and dash of milk.
Mash and add salt and pepper.
Fry ground beef and drain.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup and vegetables.
Heat until warm.
Pour into baking dish and spread mashed potatoes over mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in salted water; drain and mash.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery in butter.
Add eggplant and cook five minutes.
Grate hard-cooked egg and chop livers; add to mixture. Stir in raw egg, bread crumbs, cayenne and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook a few minutes.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: savory grilled potatoes
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasonings in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and onion to coat.
Divide potato mixture evenly among 6 (12-inch) square pieces of heavy-duty foil. Seal each to form pocket.
Place foil packets on grill over medium hot coals.
Grill, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: quick pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until bread springs back when lightly touched.
Cool 20 minutes.
Turn out onto cooling rack.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix 1/3 cup soup, 1/4 cup milk, onion and parsley.
Dip chicken parts in soup mix, then roll chicken in stuffing mix. Place in baking dish.
Pour butter over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Combine balance of soup and milk and heat thoroughly. Pour over chicken just before serving.

title: fish cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375° or preheat broiler, if broiling is preferred.

Combine cereal and broth in small saucepan and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens. Remove cereal mixture from heat and add fish, pepper, onion powder, egg white and mustard, mashing with a fork until well blended. When cool enough to handle, shape into 4 patties and place on a baking sheet.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco sauce in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer sour cream and taco sauce mixture, shredded lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and black olives.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes. Makes 4 loaves or you can bake in round coffee cans.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, salt and peanut butter.
Beat in sugars and eggs.
Add flour and soda.
Mix well.
Chill until dough is firm.
Form into 1-inch balls; flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute and add 1 Hershey Kiss per cookie.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and seasoning mix; dredge chicken in seasoned crumbs and place in greased baking dish.
Saute green onions in butter; stir in whipping cream and remaining ingredients and cook until cheese melts.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: peach melba ice cream pie(makes 8 servings)
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust.
Mound vanilla ice cream and sorbet alternately.
With spatula, mound slightly toward center. Freeze overnight. Mix fruit before serving slightly softened pie. Top with whipped cream. Enjoy.

title: sweet relish
directions: Place all vegetables in large pot.
Sprinkle top with salt. Cover and let stay overnight.
Place in colander to drain; pressing to remove all liquid.
Place back in kettle.
Add sugar, seasonings and vinegar.
Mix and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack into hot sterile jars.
Do not use too much juice when packing.
Vegetables can be chopped in food processor.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add milk, beaten egg yolks, margarine and vanilla.
