Cover; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix butter, flour and walnuts together.
Grease an 8 x 13-inch glass dish and bake mixture for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 10x sugar and Cool Whip together until smooth and spread over baked crust.
Cool for 2 hours.
Mix puddings and milk together.
Add to cake and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle walnuts (chopped) on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook beef until lightly browned.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours or high heat 5 to 6 hours.

title: saucy barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion and salt.
Mix well; shape into 15 meatballs, 1 1/2-inches in size.
Arrange in microwave-safe pie plate.
Combine catsup, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Spoon over meatballs.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes.
Serves about 5.

title: apple-carrot bake
directions: Combine carrots and 1/2 cup water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain carrots and set aside.
Combine sugar and flour; set aside.
Layer half each of carrots and apples in a lightly greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with half of flour mixture and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Repeat procedure.
Drizzle with orange juice and ginger, mixed together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Toss before serving.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: party carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all cake ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean and cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool.
Remove from pan after 30 minutes or leave in pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: festive frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip with a fork.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Add brown and white sugar and margarine. Stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda salt and cocoa together.
Add flour to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add about 1/2 of chips to cake mix.
Sprinkle rest on top. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl 2 cups sugar, 2 cups self rising flour.
Set aside.
In saucepan, boil 1 minute 1 cup water, 1 stick margarine, 1 cup Wesson oil, 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour hot mixture over first mixture.
Stil well.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, 2 eggs. Beat slightly before adding 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients until fluffy.
Place one vanilla wafer into each muffin tin.
Add 1 tablespoon filling onto wafer. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
When cool, place 1 tablespoon of pie filling on top.

title: easy cornbread casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons shortening in extra large cast-iron skillet.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Heat and time vary on type and size of skillet.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and cream alternately.
Add vanilla.
Place in greased tube pan in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch, pineapple, vinegar and soy sauce to boiling, then add pepper and onion.
Put over rice.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Mix soda and tomato soup; add to shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients; stir until well blended.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss and serve with dressing.

title: the christ child's birthday cake
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together twice and set aside.
Cream in a large bowl the shortening and white sugar.
Add eggs to sugar mixture.
Sprinkle a small amount of dry ingredients over nuts. (This helps spread nuts more evenly through mixture.)
Add alternately the dry ingredients and buttermilk to sugar mixture; blend thoroughly.
Stir in jam and add black walnuts; mix well. Grease a 10-inch angel food pan.
Line pan with waxed paper, then grease waxed paper.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool thoroughly before icing.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger; drain grease.
Add mushrooms. Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook macaroni, layer meat mixture with cheese and macaroni.

title: french onion dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine soup, cream, mayonnaise and soup mix. Cover; chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables or potato chips.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: cheesy vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place breads on ungreased cookie sheet. Spread 2 tablespoons tomato sauce on each pita.
Divide vegetables among breads evenly.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake about 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.
tags: shredded no fat Mozzarella type cheese

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt the margarine.
Blend in flour. Add milk. Stir over medium heat until thick. Add cheese, salt and pepper. Cook until cheese is melted.
Spread some cheese sauce, then potatoes and onion, more sauce, more potatoes and ending with sauce.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread platter with cream cheese. Drain 2 cans of shrimp. Spread on cheese.
Top with tomato cocktail sauce.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Sift together flour and soda.
Combine sifted mixture with first 3 ingredients and add vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch pan greased with margarine, no flour.

title: date nut bread
directions: Add melted shortening to dates.
Add sugar and hot water; let cool.
Beat egg and add to mixture.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add to the mixture.
Stir well and add molasses. Stir well and add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage balls a la felix
directions: Mix up ahead of time.
Mix ingredients.
Make little balls and place on cookie sheet.
Freeze them.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake, without thawing, at 450° for 15 minutes or until done (well browned).

title: chili dumplings
directions: Stir chili powder into tomato juice.
Add to flour; mix well. Drop by tablespoons into simmering beef stew.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Do not lift lid.
Makes 8 to 10 dumplings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix together well the mayonnaise, oil, buttermilk, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add flour, soda, cloves, cinnamon and cocoa.
Mix and add zucchini. Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bag, add all ingredients, close bag and shake.
Empty into a shallow baking dish.
Bake about 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges together.
Mix in sugar.
Add English walnuts.
Chill to set.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in 8 x 8-inch square baking pan.

title: sweet treat
directions: Spread peanut butter on saltine crackers.
Put one marshmallow on each cracker.
Bake in oven on cookie sheet until marshmallows melt.
Serve while hot!
Yum! Yum!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken with celery and onion; debone and save some juice to add to mixture.
Mix the chicken, green pepper, celery, Cheez Whiz and soups together; put in a medium size roaster.
Melt the oleo and add garlic salt.
Put the cubed bread into oleo and garlic salt mixture.
Stir until bread is moistened and put on chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pork tenderloin a la asparagus
directions: Pound pork to flatten. In skillet, brown tenderloin in butter. Set aside. In same skillet, blend together soup and milk; stir in remaining ingredients. Return meat to skillet. Cover and simmer 40 to 45 minutes. Serve sauce atop meat. Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Mix sauce, horseradish, vinegar and garlic in large bowl with lid.
Add ribs.
Cover and shake very well.
Refrigerate for 2 hours shaking once an hour.
Grill on medium temperature until well done in middle, approximately 20 minutes.
Brush on remaining sauce before removing from grill.
(You can also use with steak and pork chops.)

title: plum nutty cake
directions: In large bowl mix dry ingredients together.
Beat in oil, eggs and plums.
Beat with mixer about four minutes or until well blended.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in tube pan in 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Glaze with 1/2 cup confectioners sugar and water.

title: christmas tree solution
directions: Fill 2/3 of bucket with hot water.
Mix in the rest.
This is supposed to help fireproof the tree.

title: sno-ball cake
directions: May use strawberries instead of pineapple.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with soups, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Cook 8 to 9 hours on slow in crock-pot, or 3 hours on high.
Add shredded cheese last half hour.

title: ripe cucumber pickles(slippery jims)
directions: Peel, cut cucumbers into strips.
Let strips stand overnight in salt and water.
Drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and 1 tsp. salt in large kettle; add soaked cucumber strips and cook until transparent with remaining ingredients which have been put in a cheesecloth bag.
Place in jars and seal; process in hot water bath for approximately 10 minutes.

title: lisa's yummy carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Blend oil, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pineapple, carrots and coconut.
Pour batter equally into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 22 to 28 minutes.
Let cool before removing from pans.
Let cool totally before frosting.
Frost with Sue's Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: apple butter
directions: Boil cider in kettle until only 2 quarts remain, about 1 1/4 hours.
Add apples.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until apples are soft, about 1 hour.
Press apples through sieve or food mill.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently, until no liquid separates from pulp, about 2 hours.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Seal and process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Makes a great gift and your house smells heavenly!

title: papaya seed dressing from mama's fish house, maui
directions: In blender or food processor, blend papaya seed until the size of ground pepper.
Blend in onion.
Add other ingredients and blend well.

title: mom's scalloped corn
directions: Drain liquid from corn into measuring cup; add milk or cream to measure 1 cup.
Melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Slowly add liquid and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and add drained corn.
Slowly add beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs and sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Place in a shallow pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(Recipe may be doubled.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter and let cool. Beat eggs and add sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add pecans, as desired, and put in unbaked pie shell crust. Bake at 300° until firm.

title: holiday delight
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Chill an hour before serving.
May also be stored in freezer.

title: homemade "shake & make" oven frying mix
directions: Combine bread crumbs, chicken broth, paprika, poultry seasoning, onion powder, oregano, rosemary, celery salt, pepper and garlic powder in a tightly covered moisture-proof container. Stir until well mixed. Use about 1 tablespoon on the mixture per serving of cut-up chicken parts. Moisten chicken in tomato juice before shaking with the crumb mixture if preferred over moistening with water.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well; pat into a loaf.
Put in baking dish and bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chicken in the garden
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken, vegetables, water chestnuts, soup and milk; mix well.
Add 1 cup onion rings. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes. Uncover and top with remaining onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: refried beans
directions: Rinse beans and remove any discolored ones.
Soak beans overnight in water well above top of beans.
In the morning, drain water and put beans in a large pot, covering with water a couple of inches above beans.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and cook until tender, checking water level so beans won't dry out or burn.
Cool beans and drain, saving the juice.
Puree the beans in food processor using a small amount of bean juice so they blend to a very smooth consistency.
Slice the onion and puree with each processorful of beans.
This recipe makes 15 to 20 servings.
You may want to divide the beans in half and prepare half on another day.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Grease 3-quart casserole dish and put ingredients in as listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
When rice is done, everything else is done.

title: baked chicken in sauce
directions: Mix together and pour over chicken.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with rice.

title: impossible pizza pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Sprinkle 2/3 cup onion and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese in plate.
Beat eggs, milk and baking mix until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake 20 minutes.
Spread sauce over top.
Layer remaining ingredients on sauce.
Bake until cheese is light brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix cabbage and green onions and refrigerate.
In small skillet melt oleo and break apart noodles; fry, stirring often, until they are golden brown.
Rake noodles out of butter.
Add slivered almonds to butter and fry about 1 minute, stirring continually.
Drain noodles and almonds on paper towel.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix vegetables and salt with 2 trays ice and let stand for 3 hours, drain and remove garlic.
Combine vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to boil, add vegetable mixture.
Heat about 5 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix well (beat quite a while), then pour into 3 round cake pans.
Swirl in some chocolate mixture in each pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool.

title: gail's cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter 5 to 7 minutes.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pork and rice(hot dish)
directions: Cut pork steak into small pieces.
Fry until tender.
In the meantime, cook your rice according to directions on box.
Add rice and peas to meat.
Pour in gravy and serve.
Real good, easy and quick supper.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients all together and pour into a casserole dish. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine flour, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender. Set aside.
Fill buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish with sliced apples.
Sprinkle topping over apples, spreading evenly to edge. Bake at 375° until golden and crisp (about 30 to 40 minutes).

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Mix the yeast mixture, salt, butter, eggs and sugar.
Add flour to make stiff dough.
Let rise for 7 hours.
Roll out and cut doughnuts.
Let rise 40 minutes.
Drop into hot oil and cook until golden brown. Dip into a glaze of powdered sugar and enough water to make a syrup. Always cool standing up sideways.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Melt butter and chocolate in pan over low heat.
Remove and cool.
Blend in sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Beat 1 minute.
Add nuts and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: italian sausage empanadas
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt mixture until it forms pea sized balls. Add iced water to flour mixture until ball forms. Knead mixture slightly by hand and set aside in refrigerator while preparing the filling.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat the eggs and powdered sugar in electric mixer for 15 minutes. Spread over graham cracker mixture. Cover in order with sliced bananas, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip. Top with pecans and maraschino cherries. Refrigerate overnight.

title: american chop suey
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown and drain hamburg; add garlic, green pepper and sauce.
Cook over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes. Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: pepper steak in the crock
directions: Spray bottom and sides of crock-pot with nonstick oil. Put all ingredients in crock and mix well. Cook on low 8 to 9 hours. Serve with noodles or rice.

title: tomato provecale
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and remove seeds.
Heat oil in a skillet ans saute tomatoes (cut side down) for three minutes.
Add garlic and saute till tomaotoes are tender.
Turn and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place tomatoes on a serving plate.
Toast bread crumbs till golden in a skillet and sprinkle over tomatoes.

title: old fashioned sorghum cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and sorghum; beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with thirds of the sour milk.
Beat until smooth after each addition.
Chill dough before rolling on well floured surface.
Roll dough in 1/4-inch sheet and cut with a 4-inch cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: *If using self-rising flour, only use 1/4 teaspoon of soda and omit the salt and baking powder.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add cup of oleo.	Dissolve soda in sour cream and add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and beat well. Chill overnight.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown on bottom.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Break eggs in bowl and whip until combined.
Add potatoes, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend well.
Add half and half, then stir well.
Ladle this filling into the pastry shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 300° and bake approximately 30 minutes longer or until a toothpick inserted 1 inch from the pie's center comes out clean.
Remove pie from oven and cool on rack.

title: new potatoes with garlic
directions: Wash and place potatoes in a large saucepan. Add other ingredients, fill pot with water to cover potatoes. Boil until potatoes are done, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat, let set in seasoned water for about 2 hours. Bring to a boil before serving. Serve with butter, salt, pepper, and sour cream.

title: calzones
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, oil and 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead 5 minutes on lightlly floured surface.
Cover and let rest 5 minutes.
Spray large cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine onion, cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour margarine over chicken; bake at 350°, 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on low heat.
Beat egg whites until firm and add 4 teaspoons sugar and beat again.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until egg whites are golden brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Make small balls of dough; roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Bake on ungreased pan at 400°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layered:
Crumble the cauliflower into small enough pieces to eat.
Place thin sliced red onion on top of cauliflower.
Crumble bacon on top of onion.
Spoon mayo on top of bacon, about 1/2-inch thick.
Then sprinkle Parmesan cheese 1/2-inch on top of mayo.
Do not mix yet.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight; before serving, mix.
Serve cold.

title: best pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately.
Add vanilla.
Put into greased, floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350 degrees until done (approximately 1 1/2 hours).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil, and vanilla. Add zucchini, then add flour sifted with salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Add 1 cup nuts (more or less). Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour or until done at 350°. If using glass pans, reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: blueberry scones
directions: Adjust rack to center of oven and heat to 400°. Spray a baking sheet with cooking spray and set aside.

title: tennessee white chili
directions: Combine the beans, broth, garlic and 1 onion in soup pot. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Saute the other onion in the margarine until tender.
Add the chilies and seasonings.
Mix well and add this to the cooked beans.
Add the chicken and simmer at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
This may be served with grated sharp Cheddar cheese and cornbread.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Clean broccoli and remove stems.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Steam in 1/2 cup of water until tender.
Do not drain.
Set aside. Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour to make a roux.
Cook for 2 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken stock, stirring with a wire whip and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low.
Add broccoli, half and half, salt and pepper.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: The Colonel claims that his chicken is "finger lickin' good," this recipe should pull rank on the colonel every time.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first six ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon over potatoes (spread) and cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix cornbread, milk and oil.
Stir in beaten eggs, both cans of corn, sugar and 1 1/2 c. cheese.
Pour mixture into a greased 11 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes then top casserole with remaining cheese and bake 20 minutes more.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: fried peach pie mix
directions: Cook until thick. Freezes well.

title: coke cake frosting
directions: Boil butter, cocoa and Coke; remove from heat.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well; if a little stiff, add a little water.

title: farmers drop oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugars, oil, eggs and cream.
Add soda, spices, salt, oatmeal, nuts, raisins and 1 cup flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining flour, beating after each cup.
These cookies should not spread, but remain upright.
Drop by tsp. onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
These cookies are soft and will remain that way if stored in tightly covered container.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Drain the oil from the tuna fish.
Flake it with a fork and add the rest
of the ingredients.
Blend well and serve on crispy lettuce
leaves.
Add
sliced
tomatoes,
if
desired. Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix to directions on box, except cut back 2 1/2 tablespoons water and add 3 tablespoons of creme de menthe.
About 3 drops green coloring can be added for color.
Bake and cool.
Spread Hershey's fudge topping.
Top with Cool Whip that has 3 drops of green coloring folded in and 2 tablespoons creme de menthe.

title: okra stew
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef.
Set aside and if necessary, pour off fat.
Combine okra, onion, tomatoes and tomato sauce in Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Saute for 10
minutes.
Add meat and seasonings to vegetables, mixing well.
Simmer over medium heat about 20 additional minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Excellent with corn bread.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken generously with garlic salt.
Roll each piece in cornstarch.
Dip into beaten eggs.
Saute in small amount of cooking oil until brown.

title: kringla
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream sugar and margarine. Add egg; mix well.
Add milk; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla; mix.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: boneless breast and thighs
directions: Dilute soup with milk.
Place chicken in baking dish, cover with Swiss cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: triple layer mud pie
directions: Melt chocolate and mix with condensed milk.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Top with pecans.
In a separate bowl, mix cold milk with pudding mix.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups of the pudding mixture over the pecans in the pie crust.
To the remaining pudding, add half of the Cool Whip.
Mix and spoon into the crust.
Top with the remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: turkey and spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients in casserole except cheese.
Put grated cheese on top and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: avocado sauce
directions: Grate on fine side of grater the cayenne peppers into the avocado, which is already mashed. Add all other ingredients. Blend together well. Taste for flavor; if you want it more spicy, add more grated pepper for desired taste. You may use jalapeno or other hot peppers, but they don't give the same good flavor that cayennes do. Store any leftovers in small tightly covered container in fridge. Makes 4 servings. Preparation time: 0:30.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Work in pecans.
Melt wax and chocolate together.
Let cool.
Roll candy balls and drop in chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Marinate vermicelli overnight in lemon juice, oil and Accent. Add chopped onions, celery, bell pepper, olives, pimentos and mayonnaise.
Salt to taste.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken into pieces. Put ingredients together with 1 stick of melted margarine. Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes or until crackers are brown and casserole is bubbly.

title: salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a glass jar or covered container. Shake well to make sure everything is well blended.

title: salmon-caper spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill to improve flavor.
Serve on crackers or thin slices of rye bread.
You'll love this even if you think you don't like salmon!

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, season and brown ground meat and onion.
Drain and add taco sauce and mix well.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put layers of tortillas.
Top with meat mixture, then cheese.
Add another layer of tortillas, enchilada sauce (1/2 can), meat and cheese.
Last layer of tortillas, enchilada sauce and cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: hints
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add water until smooth.

title: taiwanese special
directions: Heat pan; add oil and pork.
Fry until done.
Add onions. Saute; add cabbage and toss.
Add sugar, ginger and peppers. Add salt if necessary.
Heat thoroughly and serve at once with rice, boiled noodles or crisp noodles.
Vegetables should be crunchy; do not overcook.
If liquid forms, thicken it with 1 tablespoon cornstarch mixed with 1/4 cup water.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Sprinkle rice over chicken. Season with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water; pour over chicken and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours, or until chicken is done.

title: flat bread
directions: Knead until smooth.
Divide into 8 balls and knead each ball until smooth and round.
With a rolling pin, flatten each until 1/4-inch thick and about 4 or 5-inches in diameter.
Cover with a towel and let rise 45 minutes.
Arrange the rounds upside down on baking sheet.
Bake at 500° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown and puffed in center.
The breads will be hard when they come from oven, but will soften and flatten when cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In pan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Add broth and stir to mix well.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and pimento.
Heat until once again bubbly. Place biscuits on top of hot chicken mixture and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits are light brown.

title: better than anything cake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan bake cake according to package directions. Meanwhile in saucepan combine pineapple with juice and sugar; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until thick and syrupy, about 20 minutes.
When cake is done, remove from oven and pierce top with a fork at 1 inch intervals.
Pour in pineapple mixture and spread over cake; cool completely.
In medium bowl combine pudding mix with milk; blend until thick.
Spread over cake.
In medium bowl beat Cool Whip until soft peaks form.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla; continue beating until stiff. Spread over pudding.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving; sprinkle with coconut if desired.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Blend all dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture with milk and cherry juice.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Pour batter into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove bread from pan at once. Cool before slicing.
Makes 36 (1/2-inch slice) pieces of bread.

title: smoked oyster spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve on snack crackers.

title: dip
directions: Blend with whip or mixer. Good with fresh vegetables.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and cover.
Leave overnight in refrigerator.
Mix remaining ingredients and toss.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Pour dressing over salad and toss before serving.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in double boiler.
Add powdered sugar and water.
Mix well.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Cook all vegetables in water until tender.
Mash vegetables and add soup (mix with milk) and heat until cheese is melted in soup.

title: meat loaf(published in southern living)
directions: Combine bread and milk in small bowl.
Allow to soak 5 minutes.
Combine beef, onion, eggs, salt and bread mixture; mix well.
Shape meat mixture into a loaf.
Place in lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: gail's dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread chili sauce on top of cream cheese.
Top with grated cheese
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: greek squash
directions: Cook squash until tender in slightly salted boiling water. Drain and mash.
Mix torn bread, milk, cheese and beaten egg well.
Stir in squash.
Use 1/2 stick margarine to dot bottom of casserole dish.
Pour in squash mixture.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil on high for 3 minutes the sugar, milk, cocoa, vanilla and butter.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Spread in 8 1/2 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 2/3 cup Pet milk.
Beat at high speed until well mixed.
Place 1/2 of mix in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Press in bottom and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup Pet milk and pour over crust.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Flatten rest of cake dough by putting between wax paper and pressing to the size of pan.
Remove from wax paper. Cover the entire surface of chips and nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: shrimp dill
directions: Over low heat, melt butter; add and heat shrimp and mushrooms. Mix together the sour cream, salt, paprika, Worcestershire sauce and dill seed.
Pour over shrimp and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring, until just heated and add lemon juice.
Serve over rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Cut banana and nuts into small pieces and add.
Sift flour with salt and baking soda and add to mixture.
Bake in greased loaf pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine pumpkin, sugar, eggs, milk and spices. Pour into a sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Make topping by combining dry cake mix with the margarine. Sprinkle topping on the pumpkin mixture. Bake for 1 hour.

title: crockpot chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, eggs, water and oil. Mix with electric mixer on medium for 2 minutes. Stir in chocolate chips. Pour cake into greased crockpot. Cover and cook on low for 6-7 hours or on high for 3-4 hours or until a toothpick comes out with moist crumbs. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lefse(norwegian)
directions: Mix all together except flour.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Just before you are ready to bake add flour and roll very thin.
Use 1/2 cup dough or less for each lefse.
Bake at 450° or 500° on lefse grill.
Turn once.
Holiday family favorite.

title: cherry winks
directions: Blend dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs, then milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add pecans, dates and 1/3 cup chopped cherries.
Blend in dry ingredients, mixing well. Roll approximately 1 teaspoon dough into ball and coat with corn flakes by rolling.
Bake on greased cookie sheet, after topping each cookie with 1/4 cherry at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon herb dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Can be used as salad dressing or over fish and chicken as a marinade.

title: deer stew
directions: Cook ground deer meat.
Cover potatoes, carrots, onion and butter with water.
Let boil.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, corn, cooked meat, macaroni and paprika.
Cook for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves about 8.

title: sugar-free muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Slightly beat eggs and add to flour mixture.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into muffin tins and bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.
May also use tube pan or loaf pans and adjust time accordingly.

title: low calorie soup
directions: Cut up ingredients and put in a large pan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil, then boil for 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
More water may be needed during cooking.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook together sugar, syrup and water to a hard ball stage (250°).
Add peanuts and butter and cook to a light caramel color (about 7 1/2 minutes over medium heat).
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda.
Stir quickly and pour out on buttered foil. Let cool.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil. Add hamburger and brown. Drain off excess fat.
Cook shells according to package directions. Drain. Add shells to meat mixture. Add tomato sauce, corn and seasonings.
Mix well. Transfer to 2-quart casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and orange segments. In large bowl, combine pineapple, orange segments, banana, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add cheese.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and stir to form soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured board. Roll to about 1/4 to 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter or a tomato sauce can with both ends removed (8 ounces).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or lightly brown.
Makes about 18.

title: german potato salad
directions: Layer potatoes, celery and onions, then top with part of mixture.
Make about 3 layers.

title: brownies for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into an 11 x 14-inch pan sprayed with Pam or greased with Crisco.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread icing on brownies when cool.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Slice tops of pepper; take out seeds and wash.
Place peppers in enough hot water to cover them; cook for 5 minutes.
Cook hamburger and onion together until meat is done; drain off grease. Add remaining ingredients; heat.
Fill peppers with stuffing. Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Uncover; cook for about 10 minutes.

title: margaret's biscuits
directions: Blend Crisco and flour.
Add milk; mix well.
Knead and roll out on floured surface.
Cut and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: garden zucchini bisque
directions: In 3 quart saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter; add zucchini, mushrooms, onions and parsley.

Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisply tender, 6 to 8 minutes. Meanwhile in 2 quart saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter over medium heat; stir in flour until smooth and bubbly; add chicken broth.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until soup is thickened, 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in cream, pepper and zucchini mixture.
Continue cooking until heated through, 5 to 6 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl; blen well.
Stir in remaining ingredients, drop by rounded tablespoonful, about 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press 3 to 4 M&M's in each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes; cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: low-fat carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry items, then add remaining items and mix well. Spray 8-inch cake pan with Pam and pour all mixture into it.
Cook 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown meat; simmer 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Cook noodles.
Put 3/4 noodles in casserole dish; pour meat mixture over noodles.
Top with onions, sour cream and cream cheese mixture.
Cover with rest of noodles.
Put 1 cup of grated cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: orange delight cake
directions: Mix with beater 1 minute.
Put in ungreased jelly roll pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, oats, salt and vanilla.
Drop with spoon on wax paper.
Cool completely.

title: smoked turkey cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Shape into 1 to 2 balls.
Roll in pecans.
Wrap well; freeze or refrigerate.

title: large polish cookies
directions: Dough will be stiff.
Shape between palms of your hands and roll like a clothes pin and lap ends together.
Bake 15 minutes until light brown.
Ice with colored icing and put sprinkles on top.

title: snowballs
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients; then add the next 3 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly with hands and form into 1-inch balls. On an ungreased pan bake at 325° for 15 minutes (do not brown). Roll in confectioners sugar while still hot.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: cream of roasted garlic soup
directions: Place garlic heads on cookie sheet, sprinkle with olive oil and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour.
Let cool.
Cut off end of each clove and squeeze out contents; set aside.

Saute onion and leeks in the butter until tender and translucent. Stir flour into onion mixture until all butter is absorbed and continue to cook the mixture over low heat for 4-5 minutes, stirring constantly. Slowly add chicken stock, stirring with wire whisk until smooth, and bring mixture to a simmer. Process potatoes in a blender or food processor.
Add to soup, mixing thoroughly.
Finish the soup by adding the cognac and the cream, and seasoning to taste with salt and white pepper.
Heat thoroughly. Serve immediately garnished with croutons.
Yield:
2 quarts.

title: quick chick and noodle soup
directions: Place a large pot over medium heat; add oil. Work close to stove and add vegetables to the pot as you chop, in order they are listed. Add bay leaves and season vegetables with salt and pepper to taste. Add stock to pot and raise flame to bring liquid to boil. Add diced chicken; return soup to boil. Reduce heat to moderate. Cook chicken 2 minutes and add noodles. Cook soup additional 10 minutes or until noodles are tender. Stir in parsley and serve.

title: life's recipe
directions: Fold in 4 cups prayer and faith.
Mix thoroughly and serve with a smile.

title: mike's bread
directions: Pour 1 pint boiling water over corn meal, wheat cereal and oatmeal.
Cool to 100°.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and add to mixture.
Stir well.
Add honey, 1 cup warm water and salt. Stir in whole wheat flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
When the dough is too stiff to stir with a spoon, use your hands.
Add enough flour to make a sticky dough.
Knead on a floured board for 5 minutes (dough will be sticky).

title: tart pineapple pie
directions: Squeeze juice of lemons and limes into a bowl.
Add sweetened milk; drain pineapple and add to mixture.
Add food color, if desired.
Place in pie shell and top with whipped cream.
Chill for at least 3 hours.

title: butterscotch thins
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and butter over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Beat in brown sugar and egg.
Sift flour and baking soda together; stir into butterscotch mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Chill.
Shape into 12-inch roll.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill thoroughly (or wrap in foil and freeze).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Unwrap dough and slice very thin.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from baking sheet.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and pour in graham cracker crust.
Put half tub of Cool Whip on top of pie.

title: baked rice casserole
directions: Combine in saucepan rice, water, tomatoes, pepper and salt. Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and cook until rice is soft, about 20 minutes.
Add oleo; set aside.
Fry beef and onions in small amount of oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Combine soup, Cheddar cheese and milk in saucepan.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add chopped olives.
Place all ingredients in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or place in a crock-pot and cook for 1 hour on high.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Pour water over bran and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add milk and flour alternating with soda and salt.
Add Grape-Nuts and bran last. Bake in greased muffin tin filled half full for 12 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
If batter is chilled, raise temperature to 425°. Keeps in refrigerator 6 weeks.

title: chicken salad ham rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients except ham and lettuce. Spread mixture on ham slices and roll each one up, insert tooth pick and place them seam side down on bed of lettuce leaves.

title: cornbread ring(microwave)
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, milk and cooking oil.
Beat until smooth, about 1 minute.
Place onions and cheese in well-greased 8-inch ring mold.
Tilt to coat all sides, reserving excess crumbs.
Pour batter into ring mold and sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Microwave at Medium-high (7) for 9 to 11 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Turn out on cooling rack or serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large 2 1/2-quart salad bowl, layer lettuce, mushrooms, onions and peas.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and curry powder. Spread over salad to seal.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Top with bacon before serving.
Serves 8.

title: spinach salad with strawberries
directions: Mix vinegar and preserves.
Add oil.
Toss spinach with dressing and half of strawberries, kiwi and nuts.
Sprinkle remaining on top.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Directions For Feeding Starter:
Remove Starter from the refrigerator and uncover.
In a separate bowl, mix 3/4 cup sugar, potato flakes and 1 cup warm water.
Add this to the Starter and leave uncovered on the counter all day.
In the early evening you will be ready to make the bread dough.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed. Boil chicken until tender enough to take off bone. Add onion and mushroom soup to cheese. Add macaroni; season to taste with chicken added. You can serve from stove top, or if you desire put ingredients in pan or dish and bake for 20 minutes, covered.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Place peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme in bowl.
Cook sugar and milk to soft ball.
Remove from heat and pour over other mixture.
Beat vigorously until smooth.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: chili verde
directions: In large skillet, brown pork (cut into bite-size pieces) in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add all other ingredients and cook for about 2 minutes.
Add water, enough to cover all meat.
Simmer for 1/2 hour, stirring once in awhile.
Add more salt, if needed.

title: my favorite english peas
directions: Open the peas and drain liquid in 2-quart pot.
Set peas aside.
Peel the potatoes and slice thin and put in pot with liquid.
May add carrots, if desired. Slice the onion thin and add to liquid. Add enough water to cook vegetables, but not a lot of water.
When vegetables are done, add the soup, peas and ham. Let cook until flavors are mixed.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix all together and chill ahead of time.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and Karo syrup in microwave-safe bowl. Cook until it boils.
Stir, reset and cook 2 1/2 minutes more. Take out and add 1/4 teaspoon soda.
Pour over popcorn in a brown paper bag.
Cook 1 minute.
Take out and shake.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes more.
Pour out on a cookie sheet to cool.

title: grandma joe's sugar cookies(school boy jumbles)
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; gradually add beaten eggs and liquid.
Add flavorings.
Sift and measure flour; add baking powder and re-sift.
Stir into mixture.

title: hot slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and cook with 1 teaspoon salt and enough water to cover it.
Cook until tender and drain.
Combine sour cream, eggs, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat enough to mix.
Pour drained cabbage back into large pan it was cooked in and melt butter with cabbage in pan.
Pour sour cream mixture along with 2 tablespoons vinegar over cabbage.
Simmer, but do not boil, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Tastes even better the next day, reheated slowly.
Be careful not to boil, as it scorches easily.

title: cubed steaks with peppers
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
In large skillet brown meat on both sides in hot oil, drain off fat.
Add undrained tomatoes, the green peppers, onion, basil, oregano and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove meat to serving platter. Blend together cold water and flour.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more.
Serve mixture over meat.

title: spiced holiday nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl mix all spices together. Set aside.
Heat oil in a nonstick skillet over low heat.
Add spices and stir well.
Simmer 3-4 minutes to mellow flavors. Place nuts in a bowl.
Scrape mixture onto nuts and toss well. Spread nuts in one layer on a baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes, shaking pan once or twice.
Remove from oven.
With a rubber spatula, toss nuts with any spices and oil on the bottom of the pan.
If desired, sprinkle with a bit more garlic salt.
Let rest for 2 hours in a cool place.
Store in air tight jars.

title: crescent roll dogs
directions: Cut out the crescent shapes and line the dough with half a slice of cheese.
Lay hot dog on top and wrap crescent around hot dog.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in the oven at 375° for about 10 minutes.
(Make sure an adult is there to help you with the oven.)

title: broccoli and shrimp fritters(low-fat)
directions: In medium bowl, beat the egg whites with a fork until frothy. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Coat a large frying pan with Pam. Let warm over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Drop small rounded tablespoons of the egg mixture into the pan and cook for 2 minutes or until browned underneath.
Flip and cook on the other side for 2 to 3 minutes or until just set.
Great as a finger food.

title: kraft fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to full, rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips; flour lightly.
Brown in shortening then simmer with lid on skillet until tender.
Add bell peppers that have been cut in strips; add onions that have been sliced. Cover and simmer until onions can be cut with a fork.
Mix soup with water; add to meat mixture.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Serve hot over a bed of cooked rice.

title: chicken egg drop soup
directions: Cook onion and celery in broth until tender.
Slowly pour beaten egg into boiling broth, stirring so egg separates into shreds.
Yields 4 cups (4 servings).

title: apple pudding
directions: Spread sliced apples in 8
x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, milk and shortening into smooth batter and spread evenly over apples.

title: upside down apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread butter evenly onto bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Press pecans, rounded sides down into butter.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pat brown sugar mixture over pecans.
Place one of the prepared pie crusts on top of this mixture.
In medium bowl, combine apples, sugar, flour and Apple Bake Seasoning; toss to coat.
Place apple mixture in pie crust; spreading to make level.
Top with remaining pie crust.
Trim dough edges to 1/2 inch overhang.
Fold and roll top edge under lower edge, pressing on rim to seal securely; flute if desired.
Pierce top of crust with fork to allow steam to escape.
Bake for 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven; cool 5 minutes on wire rack.
Place serving dish over top of pie; invert.
Remove pie plate.
Serve warm or at room temperature with whipped topping flavored with Vanilla Nut Extract.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cookie bars
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 2 aluminum cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Pour over slaw and don't stir for 4 hours.
Slaw will keep well.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Melt margarine.
Cook sliced onion until clear.
Add zucchini and cook until soft.
Puree in blender and return to pan.
Add chicken soup and milk.
Heat well and serve.

title: pork marengo
directions: In skillet, brown half of the pork cubes and chopped onions at a time in hot oil.
Drain off fat.
Transfer meat and onions to crockery cooker.
In the same skillet, combine undrained tomatoes, bouillon granules, marjoram, salt, thyme and pepper. Stir together, scraping browned bits from bottom of skillet.
Pour over pork. Cover.
Cook on low heat setting for 8 to 10 hours. Turn to high heat setting. Stir in drained mushrooms. Blend cold water slowly into flour.
Stir into pork mixture. Cook, uncovered, on high heat setting until thickened, 15 to 20 minutes. Stir occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: sweet & sour pork
directions: Brown pork in small amount of fat, add 1/2 cup water and simmer for 1 hour.

title: rice - beef bake
directions: Brown meat in a little fat.
Add all other ingredients and put into a well-greased, large casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir once during cooking period.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and beat in 2 beaten eggs; cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat in 1 cup salad dressing.
Add to potatoes, eggs and chopped onion.

title: taco chili dip
directions: Mix together and bake for 20 minutes to 1/2 hour at 250°.

title: creamy pina coladas
directions: Peel and trim eyes from pineapple; remove core.
Cut pineapple crosswise into 1/2-inch slices; quarter the slices.
Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add half of pineapple and replace processor cover.
Process for 25 seconds or until pureed. Add half each of next 4 ingredients; process until smooth.
Add half of ice, processing until mixture reaches desired consistency. Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients.
Garnish each serving with coconut, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Yield: about 10 cups.

title: delicious perfection salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin in cold water; add boiling water, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Add sugar, vinegar, curry powder and cayenne pepper.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in vegetables.
Pour into 8-cup mold, chill until firm.
Serve with mayonnaise for garnish.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: grandma's coffee cake
directions: Heat milk.
After it scalds, remove from heat and add sugar, salt and butter.
When cool, add yeast mixture, eggs and flour. Knead until soft and satiny.
Let rise until double size; shape into loaves or roll out dough and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Place onto cookie sheet and allow time to rise until double size again.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: tuna and macaroni casserole(8 servings)
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Combine with tuna, salt, green pepper, cheese, pepper and pimento.
Add Cream Sauce and mix well.
Pour into individual casseroles.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly (about 20 minutes).

title: refrigerator-rise butterhorns
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water in large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add milk, sugar, salt, 1/2 cup butter and eggs and beat well.
Add half of the flour.
Beat with wooden spoon about 1 minute or until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
Turn out on floured board; round up into ball.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes or until dough is light, elastic, smooth and no longer sticky.
Cover; let rise 20 minutes.
Punch down; divide into 3 equal parts.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Combine egg, vinegar and water.
Sprinkle over dry ingredients.
Mix with a fork.
Let stand 10 minutes and roll out. Makes 4 crusts.
(I also use to make my cobblers.)

title: white fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients without stirring to 238°.
Remove from heat and add the next 3 ingredients.
Blend well.
Pack into a 9-inch square pan.
When partially cooled, cut into squares. Makes about 64 pieces.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and dash of salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles, about 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cool. Frosts two 8-inch layers.

title: spanakopita(greek spinach pie)
directions: Mix spinach, onion, eggs, crumbs, parsley, oil and cheeses in large bowl.
Melt butter.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan; dust with some bread crumbs.
Unroll phyllo and lay out 1 sheet into pan. Brush with melted butter.
Keep remaining phyllo covered with damp cloth.
Continue with 5 more sheets, brushing each with butter. Place mixture into pan; smooth top.
Arrange 6 more buttered sheets, one at a time.
Using razor blade, cut squares through top layers only.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Finish cutting squares through to bottom layers.

title: sweet potato casserole(yield:  8 to 10 servings)
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, 1/2 stick oleo, milk, salt and vanilla.
Use mixer to mix until smooth.
Pour into an 8 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, nuts and 1/3 stick melted oleo or butter.
Mix well.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add flour, juice and rind of lemons and milk.
Next, add egg yolks.
Mix all thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased custard cups or casserole dish.
Place cups in pan of water and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until brown like custard.
Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a pan and pour the remaining combined ingredients (except peaches) on top.
Add large can of sliced peaches on top with juice.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn with beaten eggs and set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Add milk and beat until smooth. Add melted butter.
Combine batter with corn and egg mixture and pour into greased casserole.
Set casserole dish in pan of hot water.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 1 hour or until custard is firm.

title: mary's white cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Mix in milk, water and flavoring.
Fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put in 3 layer pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip(good with tostitos and salsa chips)
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix refried beans and picante dip.
Spread in a dish.

title: ritz pie
directions: Mix the sugar, cream of tartar, cinnamon, hot water and nutmeg and let come to a boil.
Drop in the Ritz crackers and boil 3 minutes.
Put in pie crust and bake.

title: lemon-sugar crepes
directions: From lemons grate 1/2 teaspoon peel and squeeze 3/4 cup juice.
Cover and refrigerate.
In blender at medium speed, mix eggs, milk, flour, salt, lemon peel and 2 tablespoons melted butter until smooth.
Transfer to medium bowl; cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Whisk batter before using.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box. While cake is still hot, punch holes in cake. Mix milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake. Layer with coconut. When cooled, put Cool Whip on top of coconut. Garnish top with rest of coconut.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; cook slowly to dissolve sugar. Continue to cook to soft ball stage (236° on candy thermometer). Add peanuts and salt.
Cook to hard crack stage, stirring constantly (300°).
Remove from heat; add butter and soda.
Stir and rapidly pour on large well-greased cookie sheet.
Cool; break and place in covered container.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour half of the batter into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Put on top of cake layer, then 1 small package chocolate chips and 1 cup pecans.
Top with remaining batter; add nuts on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato cake(put your leftover mashed potatoes to good use.)
directions: In a large bowl, beat sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, and beat well.
Add potatoes, beat and add milk, continue beating. Sift dry ingredients in a separate bowl, then add gradually to mixture.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Place in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: applesauce raisin cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients to mixture a little at a time.
Add applesauce and Karo syrup.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Put in greased tube pan and bake at 300° for 2 hours or 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces. Wash and drain. Salt with 2 tablespoons salt and stir gently. Place in large glass container and refrigerate for 24 hours. Take out and drain.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add soups, tomatoes, garlic and chili powder.
Place tortillas in chicken broth for 10 minutes to moisten.
Line bottom of a large casserole baking dish with tortillas.
Spread chicken over tortillas.
Pour sauce over chicken and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix by hand.
Do not use electric mixer.

title: buttery blueberry pie
directions: *If frozen blueberries are used, omit water.

title: wolf brand chili pie
directions: Layer 2 cups corn chips, onions, 1/2 cup cheese and preheated chili in 1-quart casserole.
Top with remaining corn chips.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Continue baking 5 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: In large bowl cream together margarine, fruit sweetener and yogurt.
When well blended, beat in egg whites.
Combine dry ingredients separately and add to batter.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan which has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 16 pieces.

title: microwave burgundy beef balls
directions: In 1 1/2 quart baking dish or 8 or 9-inch pie plate, combine all ingredients except gravy mix and water.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls, leaving them in same dish.
Sprinkle meatballs with gravy mix.
Cook, covered, 5 minutes in microwave.
Add water and cook covered 3 minutes.
Serve on a toothpick.

title: russian tea
directions: When water boils, put in cloves (tied in sack). Pour over tea and steep 5 minutes. Pour in fruit juice and sugar. Taste and keep hot.

title: wild rice-apple stuffing
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat in a large skillet coated with cooking spray.
Add celery and onion; saute 3 minutes.
Add apple; saute 5 minutes or until apple is tender.
Combine apple mixture, rice and remaining ingredients in a 2-quart casserole; stir well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: rum cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar well.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted flour and mix well.
Bake in stem pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: cherry-cream top pie
directions: Bake
and
cool pastry.
Combine pie filling and cinnamon, spoon into cooled pastry.
Mix whipped topping, sugar and sour cream; there is enough topping for 2 pies.
Pour over top of pie and chill.
This topping is good on pumpkin pies.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and marshmallows.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, nuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: freezing cucumbers
directions: Place cucumbers in jars or containers.
Bring the sugar, water, salt and vinegar to a boil.
Cool.
Pour syrup over cucumbers and freeze.

title: eclair cake
directions: Place one layer of graham crackers in a 13 x 9-inch pan (ungreased).
Mix puddings with 3 cups milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 of mixture on graham crackers.
Add another layer of crackers; top with remaining mixture.
Add another layer of crackers.
Put in freezer for a couple of hours or overnight, then frost. Refrigerate.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Fry onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Cook macaroni; set aside.
When onion is done, add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper. Drain macaroni and add to tomato mixture.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.

title: stuffed zucchini squash
directions: Wash zucchini; cut off ends.
Cook in boiling water (salted) for 5 minutes.
Halve lengthwise; remove pulp with spoon.
Combine pulp with bread crumbs, cheese, onion, parsley, salt, pepper and eggs.
Fill zucchini shells.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: big bucket fried chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll or shake chicken parts in mixture.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake 1 hour uncovered at 350°.

title: macaroni-tuna salad
directions: Boil macaroni as instructed on box.
Steam peas and carrots over boiling water in colander.
Drain noodles.
Stir in mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add veggies and tuna; mix well.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Serve on a bed of lettuce with tomato wedges on the side.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
You can add radishes and cucumber.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix all together and taste.
If necessary, add more mayonnaise to make texture creamy.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage into a large saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat.
Add onion.
Cook and stir until transparent.
Drain, discarding all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Stir in flour. Cook over medium-low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles and turns golden.
Stir in milk.
Add seasoning.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
To serve, slice biscuits and spoon gravy over halves.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tofu salad
directions: Fry tofu, then cut into 1-inch cubes.
Tear lettuce leaves into pieces, then wash and dry.
Place lettuce leaves, tofu, carrots and leeks in a small bowl; chill.
Combine soy sauce, sesame oil, pepper, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Pour over salad. Toss then top with fried bacon.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; put chicken broth aside.
Pull chicken from bones and put in baking dish.
Add peas and carrots with chicken soup and 2 cans of chicken broth.
Pour over the chicken and vegetables.

title: strawberry heaven
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Break angel food cake into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cake pieces.
Mix sliced strawberries and glaze together and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: sesame chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken crosswise into 1/2 inch strips.
In a large bowl, combine sour cream, lemon juice, celery salt, worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, and garlic.
Mix well.
Add chicken to mixture, coat well and cover.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 15x10 inch jelly roll pan. In medium bowl, combine bread crumbs and sesame seeds.
Remove chicken from sour cream mixture.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange in single layer in prepared pan.
Spoon butter evenly over chicken.
Bake 40-45 minutes, or until chicken is tender and golden brown.
Serve with honey mustard.

title: j. c.'s cheese spread
directions: Mix cheese, pecans, mayonnaise and onion thoroughly.
Chill. Shape in ring mold. Serve with strawberry jam and crackers.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, adding to it the sugar and oil.
Then add the eggs, one at a time (beat well after each addition).
Then add the vanilla, pecans and sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into tube pan.
Mix the brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over the batter.
Then put rest of batter into pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: polish sausages and creamy potatoes(serves 4)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine the sliced potatoes and water. Cover.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender, stirring half the cooking time.
Drain, sprinkle with salt and set aside.

title: noah's ark clam chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients on top of the stove.

title: mandarin shrimp dip
directions: Heat curry powder and butter on medium for 1 minute.

Turn stove element to low and stir in flour, instant minced onion, dried parsley, garlic salt, sugar and instant liquid chicken broth (dissolve instant chicken broth in 1 cup hot water before adding to pot).
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly, then boil (the gentle, rolling kind) for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice, mandarin oranges and shrimp.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: spicy oven-fried catfish
directions: Use oven rack above middle of the oven.
Heat oven to 450°. Combine cornmeal, bread crumbs, salt, paprika, garlic powder, cayenne pepper and thyme.
Dip fish into milk.
Coat with cornmeal mixture.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan, coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Pour margarine over fish.
Bake, uncovered, until fish flakes very easily with fork, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham delights
directions: Split biscuits.
Spread on ham and layer with crumbled cheese. Put top of biscuits on and bake 10 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter tandy cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scald milk and butter and set aside. Mix other ingredients except peanut butter and Hershey candy bars. Add the milk and butter and beat until batter becomes thin.
Grease 1-inch deep cookie sheet.
Pour in batter and bake for 25 minutes. Spread with peanut butter immediately out of oven using as much peanut butter needed to make a nice even coating on cake.
Place in refrigerator until cool.
Melt chocolate bars and spread over cooled cake.
Spread quickly so chocolate doesn't harden. Refrigerate.
Let stand before cutting into small squares so chocolate doesn't crack.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa together.
Put in 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Add lettuce, tomato, onions, olives, peppers and Cheddar cheese to make top layer.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oreo-date dessert
directions: Crush cookies and set aside 1/2 cup crumbs.
Combine crumbs and butter to make a crust.
Press into a 10-inch square pan (dish).

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Top with pie filling.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: If using fresh broccoli, precook it (but be careful not to overcook).
Prepare rice according to package instructions.
Put broccoli in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with rice; pour soup over rice, then cover with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, cut bread into bite-size pieces and fry in butter until crisp.
Put bread on top of casserole and bake for another 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: candy(divinity)
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients.
Let stand 1 hour.
Mix and cook until fine thread forms.
Let large bubbles settle and add the vanilla. Beat the egg whites in mixing bowl.
Add syrup slowly.
Beat until loses gloss. Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: black bean 'n salsa dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 3 cups.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and juice.
Put into melted butter but do not mix.
Pour peaches with juice over flour mixture, but do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until firm on edges, but soft in center.

title: french apple cream pie
directions: Pour apple pie filling into pie shell.
Mix together pudding and buttermilk until thick.
Pour over apples.
Cover and chill. Garnish with almonds.

title: hidden valley ranch oyster crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine all ingredients and pour over crackers.
Stir to coat.
Place in oven for 15 to 20 minutes; stir gently halfway through baking.

title: applesauce-cinnamon candy salad
directions: Dissolve cinnamon candy in boiling water.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Add applesauce.
Put half in a salad mold and chill until firm, then spread cream cheese and Miracle Whip, mixed together, over the top.
Pour the other half of the Jell-O on the top.
Chill until firm.
Very good.

title: chewy bars
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake at 300°
for 45 minutes in a greased and floured pan.

title: futti
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool, debone, strain and reserve broth.
Brown ground beef, drain fat, wash rice, add to meat.
Add seasonings and pine nuts.
Add chicken broth to saucepan until mixture is just covered.
Cover and simmer approximately 30 minutes.
In separate bowl, mash 1 to 2 cloves garlic with salt to make a paste.
Add 1 cup vinegar and 2 cups chicken broth.
Toast bread and tear into bite size pieces.
In large bowl, combine chicken, meat and rice and toast.
Heat broth mixture, pour over and toss.
Season to taste.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Reserve 3/4 cup nuts.
Mix all remaining ingredients in a bowl and store in refrigerator, covered, overnight.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll in reserved nuts.

title: sugar-free pear butter
directions: In a kettle, combine water and 1/4 cup lemon juice.
Peel, core and quarter the pears, placing them in lemon juice mixture to retard browning until all have been peeled.
Drain liquid in kettle.
Add grape juice and remaining lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook until pears are soft, about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Press through a sieve or food mill or process in a blender or food processor until smooth. Return puree to kettle.
Add spices.
Cook and stir until very thick, 20 to 35 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in sweetener. Adjust sweetener to taste.
Pour into jars or plastic containers. Refrigerate up to 3 weeks.
(For longer storage time, pour hot into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Use within 3 weeks of opening.)
Yields 4 cups.

title: hamburger pie casserole
directions: Cook ground beef (nice and brown).
Put cooked ground beef in casserole dish.
Add drained can of corn on top of ground beef. Add mashed potatoes on top of corn.
Top mashed potatoes with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Grease cookie sheet and press on dough. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.
Spread the apricots on the cool dough.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil and sugar; beat well.
Stir in zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Sifted flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and spices should be sifted together.
Add to zucchini mixture and blend thoroughly.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake for about 1 hour. Yield:
2 loaves.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a casserole dish.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Put on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: canadian meat pie
directions: Place ingredients in pan; add enough water to cover.
Mix well.
Simmer 1 hour (add more water if needed).
Place in unbaked pie crust (juice must be used; it may seem excessive but it is not).
Add top crust; slit crust and bake until brown, about 50 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Makes 2 (9-inch) deep pies.
Can be frozen.
Good served warm or cold.
Good served with or without applesauce or catsup.

title: crispix snack mix
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven at 250°.
Stir in spices and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal, nuts and pretzels; mix until coated.
Bake in oven at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool. Makes 8 cups.

title: coconut ball
directions: Mix melted butter (not hot), sugar, milk, vanilla and coconut. Let cool in refrigerator (30 minutes), then shape into balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls in; take out and place on a buttered cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to juice to make a cup.
Bring to boil; add jello and let cool.
Add cream cheese and let it thicken in refrigerator.
After it sets and thickens, add all other ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream.
Let set in refrigerator about 4 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients and beat well.
Serve with: pineapple, cantaloupe, strawberries, bananas and apples.

title: holiday salad
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Spread apples, cranberries and sugar.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased square pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy (about 3 minutes).
Pour over hot crust.
Bake for 25 minutes. Cool; cut into squares.

title: bacon and eggs pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Place pizza crust on foil lined baking sheet.
Top with bacon, veggies, and cheese.
Beat eggs with 1/4 c. water and pour over crust.
Bake 15-20 minutes, or until set.

title: instant chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and sift.
Store in jars. To serve, fill cup half full of mix and finish filling with hot water.
Makes about 1 gallon mix (50 servings).

title: sunshine salad
directions: Cook mixture until thick.
Chill, then mix with 1/2 pint whipped cream or 1 package Dream Whip.
Beat cream cheese until smooth and spread on top of jello salad.

title: potluck special
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: las vegas fruit salad
directions: Mix orange juice, pudding mix and Cool Whip with electric mixer. Add sour cream and blend.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: johnny cake
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in square cake pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes and spinach
directions: In a 2-quart microwavesafe casserole, microcook the sliced potatoes, water and salt, covered, on 100% power for 8 to 10 minutes, or until potatoes are just tender, stirring twice. Drain; remove from casserole and set aside.
In small casserole, cook onion in margarine, covered, on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add milk all at once; stir to combine.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 6 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring every minute until sauce starts to thicken, then every 30 seconds. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in the cooked potatoes, spinach and pimiento.
Cook, covered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spinach, mushroom and red onion salad
directions: Whisk all ingredients in small bowl.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.)

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Keep in airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup mix to each cup of hot water to drink.
Can add more Quik if you like it more chocolatey.

title: creamy ranch dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth. Cover & chill. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Cut bacon slices into inch-size pieces and microwave.
Do not throw away grease!
Cut up the onion into small pieces and the potatoes into bite-size squares.
