The peppers need to be cut up fine.
Put all ingredients in a pot and add the water.
Season to taste.
Bring to a boil; then cut down the heat and cook until potatoes are done.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together well.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape in walnut size balls.
Place in freezer on wax paper lined cookie sheet until frozen.
Place in freezer bags until ready to use.

title: zucchini meat loaf italiano
directions: Preheat an outdoor grill for high heat and lightly oil grate. Skewer chicken breast cubes, green bell pepper pieces, onion chunks and red bell pepper pieces alternately on long skewers. Place skewered chicken and vegetables on the prepared grill. Brush with barbecue sauce. Turning and brushing with barbecue sauce frequently, cook to desired doneness.

title: decorating icing
directions: Beat together thoroughly 5 to 7 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and milk. Pour in pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, until custard begins to brown on top, then reduce heat to 325°.
Cook until custard is set (about 30 minutes).

title: italian chicken
directions: Pound chicken flat.
Place a slice of ham and cheese on each piece and top with tomato and dash of sage.
Tuck in sides, roll up in jelly-roll style, pressing to seal.

title: watermelon martinis
directions: In a blender, combine the watermelon chunks and puree. Remove pureed fruit and pour into a pitcher. Keep very cold, even a little frozen to make it icy.

title: texas cake
directions: Combine margarine, water and cocoa and bring to a boil in a saucepan. Remove from the heat and cool. Then place in a mixing bowl and beat in the flour, sugar and salt with a large spoon. In another bowl, beat together the eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and cinnamon. Combine the two mixtures and beat using a large spoon. Bake in a greased and floured jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In a medium bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
In a large bowl with a mixer at medium speed, beat peanut butter and corn syrup until smooth.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Gradually beat in milk.
Stir in flour just until moist.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: senate bean soup(yield:  8 servings)
directions: Wash beans and run through hot water until they are white again.
Put in pot with 4 quarts hot water.
Add ham hocks and boil slowly for about 3 hours, covered.
Saute onion in butter until light brown; add to bean soup.
Season to taste with salt and pepper, then serve.
(Do not add salt until ready to serve, as this toughens the beans.)

title: rotel dip
directions: Place all in double boiler and melt until smooth.
Cool and serve with chips.
Especially good with Doritos.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat the oil in a nonstick skillet and saute the green chilies and onion over low heat for 2 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, garlic powder, oregano, salt and water.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes or until thick.
Combine chicken and yogurt and place in shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Add tortilla strips on top of chicken mixture; cover with tomato sauce.
Top casserole with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 10 servings.

title: hot mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: baked cornbread dressing
directions: Bake white cornbread as directed.
Crumble when cool in a 2-quart bowl.
Lightly brown 1/2 cup chopped onions, 1/2 cup diced celery, in 1/3 cup margarine or butter.

Add 2 beaten eggs, 1/2 teaspoon black pepper and 1 teaspoon poultry seasoning to the crumbled cornbread, plus the lightly browned onions and celery. Add 1 1/4 cups of chicken or turkey stock or canned consomme. Stir and pour into a well-greased (6 or 8-inch) square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or browned to your liking.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: For gravy:
Brown 1/2 pound meat mixture; add onion, pepper, garlic, celery, seasonings and chopped cabbage.
Add 1/2 can tomato paste and cook until gravy comes back to grease.

title: cheese cake dip for fruit
directions: In a bowl, beat together the cream cheese, orange juice, powdered sugar, almond extract and vanilla. Fold in whipped topping. Serve with fresh fruit slices.

title: spicy turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine first 8 ingredients and all but 1/2 cup of chili sauce until well blended. Place in loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
To serve, spoon remaining chili sauce over top of loaf.
Garnish with the cheese.

title: ma's italian cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet 1 teaspoonful at a time 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool, then frost with white frosting (butter, confectioners sugar and milk).
Sprinkle with round multicolored sprinkles.

title: herbal bath bags
directions: Note:
Dried herbs may vary according to personal taste.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Blend on high until completely smooth.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: brown cows(from the files of robert eugene williams)
directions: In a tall glass, put about 2 scoops of ice cream.
Pour ice cold Coca-Cola on top and eat with an ice tea spoon.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat oil in heavy kettle.
Saute garlic and onions until golden.
Remove.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in mixture and brown well in the same oil, adding more if needed. Return onion to pot.
Add carrots, dill weed, wine and consomme. Cover tightly and simmer about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Melt butter.
Add mushrooms and saute 5 minutes.
Add to meat.
Mix gently and pour into large baking pan.
Crown with biscuits and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400° for 5 minutes.
Before done, brush with butter and sprinkle with cheese.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour dressing over all.
I rinse bottle with about 2 tablespoons vinegar; gives it more tang. Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps well.
Makes colorful Christmas salad.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Use an ungreased layer cake pan.
Cake is mixed and baked in same pan!

title: calypso beef salad
directions: Combine yogurt, mayonnaise and ginger.
Cover and refrigerate. Cut asparagus into 1-inch strips.
Cut oranges into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Cut into quarters.
Separate onion slices into rings. Combine with asparagus.
Place lettuce on serving platter. Alternately arrange orange wedges and asparagus pieces on lettuce. Place beef strips in center.
Sprinkle almonds over beef and then serve chilled dressing on the side.
A Colombard wine may go well with this dish.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add Wesson oil, then add one egg at a time.
Mix well after each.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Mix well. Bake in layers at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Poke holes in cake while still hot with wooden spoon.
Pour caramel ice cream topping on top of cake.
When cake cools, spread with Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle crumbled candy bar on top of Cool Whip.
Enjoy.
Serves 12.

title: antipasto
directions: Mix together; add a little oil.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 8 one-half pints.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Mix until berries are completely thawed.
Add applesauce to gelatin mixture.
Pour into mold.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain 1 quart jar of pickles.
Slice pickles into a bowl.
Add sugar and vinegar; stir.
Let set out at room temperature for 4 hours.
Put back into jars and refrigerate.

title: angel food peach cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy, about 15 minutes.
Add egg yolk, flavorings and almonds, beating until well blended.
Remove from beater and gradually add sifted flour to make a soft dough.

title: catfish court bouillon
directions: Cut fish in large pieces and season well.
Pour chopped ingredients over fish in large roasting pan.

title: frosted banana bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased 17 x 11 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until bars test done.
Cool and frost.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix butter, sugar and syrup together.
Beat eggs separate.
Add eggs to sugar mixture.
Stir, then add pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Prepare cookie sheet with melted butter, brown sugar and pecans.
Mix 2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, margarine and salt until warm (be careful not to kill yeast).
Add flour mixture and eggs.
Beat together.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto board and knead in more flour to make a soft dough.
Place in a greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Punch down and divide in half.
Roll on board about 2 feet long and 6 to 8-inches wide.
Pour melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
(Raisins, if desired.) Roll up and slice.
Place in prepared pan.
Let rise.
Place 1 tablespoon water between rolls.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: bogie biscuits and sophia snack dog treats
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out and cut into dog biscuits; pick your own shapes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and let set overnight.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease 2 layer pans or 1 large oblong pan.
Flour pans.
Sift together dry ingredients into large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise. Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended. Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove and cool.

title: wild duck
directions: Season the inside of the cavity of the dressed duck with salt and pepper.
Fill the cavity with a mixture of celery, onions, apples and potatoes, seasoned with salt and pepper.
(This helps absorb some of the wild game flavor.)
Rub the outside surface of the duck with a cut onion and bacon fat.
Place on a rack with breast down in a roaster with tight fitting lid.
Cook for one hour at 300°.
After the first hour, turn the bird with breast up and cook until tender.
Remove the cooked vegetables from the cavity (I discard these, they are too strong in flavor).
Stuff the bird with one of the following:
a highly seasoned bread dressing, cooked wild rice or sauerkraut.
Brush the outside surface of the duck with butter and put into shallow pan.
Return to oven at 350° to brown.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In pan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until soft. Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well. Bring to a boil. Cover and allow to simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
(If you're using uncooked shrimp, cook 10 to 15 minutes.)
Stir occasionally. Serve over rice. Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli in fine pieces and combine with onions and raisins.
Refrigerate.
Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar. One and half hours before serving, add dressing and bacon.
Serves 8.

title: cocoa zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, margarine and water until fluffy. Add rest of ingredients except chocolate chips.
Blend well and then add chips.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes, or until done. Makes 2 loaves.
Note:
For a change, try substituting apple or carrot for zucchini, or mix a combination of the two together. All combinations turn out well.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and flour.
Fold in nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Form 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Immediately roll in confectioners sugar. Cool and repeat confectioners sugar process.

title: strawberries in the snow
directions: Whip the first 4 items. Blend together well. Slice angel food cake. Put a small layer of cream cheese mixture on bottom of bowl. Place a layer of cake, then a layer of cream cheese mixture. Top with strawberry pie filling or any other kind of desired pie filling. Refrigerate until serving.

title: pastrami cheese ball
directions: Chop pastrami into small pieces (1/4-inch).
Add pastrami to bowl with onion, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix all ingredients.
Add cream cheese; mix all until well blended.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate until ready to serve with your favorite crackers.
Serves 12.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Beat eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Set 10 minutes.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cutouts
directions: Cream the margarine and add other ingredients in order given. Roll on floured board to desired thickness and cut into desired shapes. Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 8 minutes.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together and put in crockpot on low all day or bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Can add bacon or ham.

title: great guacamole without avocados
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8.

title: creepy jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatins in a large bowl 3 minutes or until completely dissolved. (Do not add cold water.) Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate at least 3 hours or until firm.
Dip bottom of pan in warm water about 15 seconds. Cut into Halloween or creature shapes with cookie cutters all the way through gelatin.
Lift from pan.
Makes 24 pieces.

title: old fashioned bread
directions: Place sugar over yeast; use enough water or milk to dissolve. Add milk and egg.
Add flour, shortening and salt.
Mix well.
Let rise 2 hours.
Roll out and let rise for 1 hour.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan in 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: hawaiian harvard beets(low calorie)
directions: Heat beets in juice and add cloves and pineapple; let simmer. Stir cornstarch in the reserved juice and add to the simmering beets.
Cook until thickens.
Add sugar, if desired.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Stir in enough mayonnaise to make it as moist as you like.
Serve on lettuce.
You can also use tuna.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Go to closest market in your neighborhood.
Find the section with cookie dough in it.
Take 1 package and rush home with it. Slice and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at temperature designated on package.
Cool and munch away.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: Preheat frying pan to 420°.
Fold in 2 strips of bacon.
Add 2 eggs; don't break yolk and do not mix with bacon.
After eggs are half cooked, break into little pieces.
Add precooked rice.
Don't mix with eggs and bacon.
Add cut up green onions on rice and 3 to 4 tablespoons oil.
Sprinkle soy sauce on top of rice.
Mix bacon and eggs with rice.
Push to back of pan.
Add precooked chicken to the front of pan and saute.
Mix it all together.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour Chex into a large bowl.
Drizzle chocolate mixture over Chex and stir until coated.
Put 2 cups 10x sugar in a trash bag.
Pour coated Chex in bag and shake, shake, shake!
Keeps well.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend both packages of mix together in bowl.
Add eggs and milk (premixed) and beat by hand until well mixed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Blend soup, cheese and egg; add mayonnaise and milk.
Stir into broccoli.
Chill overnight.
Melt butter.
Mix with bread crumbs.
Top casserole with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup (Campbell's)

title: make-ahead breakfast eggs
directions: In a medium bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper; set aside.
In a large skillet over medium heat, melt butter; pour in egg mixture.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are set but still moist.
Remove from heat to cool.
Stir in sour cream. Spread evenly into buttered 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 7-inch).
Top with bacon and cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Uncover eggs; bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and cheese has melted.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Beat all ingredients
with mixer until well mixed.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and sugar in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and pecan pieces.
Sprinkle this topping over berry mixture.
Dot with stick of margarine.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 55 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes or until brown.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, discard skin and bones; save liquid.
Crush fish, stir in eggs, fish liquid and potatoes or bread crumbs, blending well.
Add seasonings and lemon juice, mixing well. Divide into 1/4 cup portions and shape into flat patties, about 1/2-inch thick.
Heat shortening sizzling hot in heavy skillet. Lay in patties and brown on both sides to a rich golden color. Remove to a hot platter and garnish with parsley and lemon wedges, if desired.
May be served with tartar or celery sauce.
Makes 5 servings.

title: blondie maple butter sauce
directions: Combine syrup and butter, cook over low heat until butter is melted.
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Remove from heat and beat in cream cheese and maple extract until smooth.
Heat again either over low heat or in the microwave at short intervals to reach desired sauce consistency.
Serve over blondies topped with vanilla ice cream.
Should be enough sauce to generously top a 9 X 13 inch pan recipe.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients well; pour into pie shell.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix and bake for 20 minutes at 350° on a greased cookie sheet with 1 inch edge.
Let cake cool in pan.

title: betty's cornbread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, cornmeal, salt and baking powder. Add oil, egg and milk. Stir to mix all ingredients well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch oiled pan. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Best when served hot.

title: potato-spinach casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Top with the cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.
Can be prepared early in day and baked later.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add mayonnaise and mix well. Spread 2 slices of bread with egg mixture.
Top each with another slice of bread.
Arrange tomato slices and lettuce on top of sandwich.
Top with remaining bread.
Cut each sandwich into quarters to serve, using wooden picks to hold layers together. Yield:
2 servings.

title: skillet barbecued chicken
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
In a large skillet over medium heat, stir 1/4 cup of water and all ingredients except chicken until well combined.
Add chicken.
Cook chicken 35 minutes, turning occasionally, until evenly browned and fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: velvet fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle inside bottom of Bundt pan with some of the pecans and chocolate chips. Mix the cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream, oil, water and vanilla.
Bake in Bundt pan 1 hour or until tests done or sometimes sooner.

title: golden ginger chicken
directions: Brush chicken with salad oil.
Arrange, skin side down, in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cook in microwave oven 10 minutes, giving dish a quarter turn after 5 minutes. Combine soup, onion, orange juice and ginger.
Turn chicken, skin side up, pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Put in oven on 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir sauce after the first 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and margarine; let stand 15 minutes. Stir and add both sugars and slightly beaten eggs.
Blend.
Sift soda, cream of tartar, cocoa and flour together and add to batter. Stir until well blended.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cocoa and cake mix together.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, food coloring, margarine and eggs, beating until well moistened.
Add soda and vinegar.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Bake in two 8 or 9-inch greased and floured layer pans at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until done.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: pickled dogs
directions: Pour this over ingredients.
This is better after it sets in refrigerator a day or two.

title: ruth's caramel icing
directions: Mix the oleo or butter and brown sugar.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool slightly, then add the milk; mix well. Add the vanilla and powdered sugar.
(If too thin, add more sugar.)

title: orange pound cake(yields 20 servings)
directions: Set out butter and let come to room temperature.
Grate rind of one orange and add grated rind to butter.
Then juice orange and add enough milk to make 1 cup of liquid.
Add the pinch of baking soda (about 1/8 teaspoon) to liquid.
Stir and then set aside.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together the peanut butter, powdered sugar and butter. Make into balls and freeze for about 30 minutes.
Melt in top of double boiler the paraffin and chocolate chips.
Use toothpick to dip in chocolate.
Cool in buttered pan.

title: graham cookies
directions: Carefully break crackers in quarters according to lines. Spread with frosting on bottom.
Top with a second cracker so you have a sandwich cookie.
Serve with milk and offer to friends at tea party.
Grandmothers like them too!

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in small pieces. Beat the eggs. Add the sugar, salt and flour.
Mix well. Add the rhubarb.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Roll out dough for top crust.
Put on top.
Seal tightly the edges of the pie.
Make slits in crust to allow steam to escape.
Brush milk lightly over crust and sprinkle with sugar (optional).
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine all ingredients and fold in potatoes. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
This makes a 9 x 13-inch casserole.

title: light chicken fettuccini alfredo
directions: Heat margarine and oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, scallions, garlic and cook stirring until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir cornstarch into 2 Tbsp. of milk.
Add to the skillet with the remaining milk, romano cheese, mushrooms, tomatoes, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce the heat to medium and simmer until the sauce is slightly thick - 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in basil and remove from heat.
Toss the hot cooked pasta with the sauce and sprinkle with 2 tsp. grated cheese and serve.

title: daiquiris
directions: Blend, then add a little half and half or milk and blend again.

title: chicken stuffed with crab
directions: Place
each
of
the
chicken breasts between sheets of plastic
wrap and pound until thin.
Try not to tear them (but don't
worry a lot).
On top of 1 side of each breast, place a bit of
crab
meat,
some
cheese,
mushrooms, onion, parsley and/or green
peppers.
Pour
some Blue cheese salad dressing (or
you might
prefer another flavor) over that combination. Place
the other
half
of
the
breast over this one and use toothpicks to stitch sandwiches together.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and peas and place in casserole.
Put remaining ingredients (except almonds or crackers) in saucepan and heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over asparagus and peas. Sprinkle with almonds or crackers.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian sausage and pasta
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage and drain. Stir in pasta and frozen vegetables. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender but crisp, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: mexican tea cakes
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 400° on lightly greased cookie sheet 10 minutes (light brown). Cool 3 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Prepare jello with fruits.
Put half of it in dish and place in refrigerator.
When it starts to gel, spread sour cream on top of congealed salad and pour on the rest of jello and fruit mixture and refrigerate, covered with Saran Wrap.

title: pear jam
directions: You will also need jelly jars, lids and rings.

title: great grandma's bread pudding
directions: Mix bread with scalded milk.
Add margarine and sugar.
Pour over eggs.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: beef, spaghetti, and cheese
directions: Trim off fat and cut beef into 2 x 1/2-inch strips. Combine 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper, and 2 tablespoons flour;
pound into meat.
Heat oil in heavy Dutch oven and brown beef quickly; remove from pan.
Brown 2 tablespoons flour in pan drippings.
Gradually stir in water and add 1/2 teaspoon salt, lemon pepper, catsup, and Worcestershire sauce.
Return steak to pan, cover and simmer over low heat for
1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with spaghetti and grated cheese.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: lemony asparagus
directions: Place cooked asparagus in shallow greased casserole in single layer.
Melt butter; heat until golden brown.
Blend in mayonnaise, seasonings and lemon juice.
Pour over asparagus. Sprinkle with crumbs, then cheese.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain strawberries, pineapple and orange slices.
Mix with pie filling and bananas.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly with fork.
Add sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in Smuckers Caramel topping and butter, mix well.
Stir in Pecan Halves.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 350 F for 45 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly on rack before serving. Cover.
Chill to store.

title: orange sangria
directions: Cut orange in half.
Take off a couple of slices, quarter them, and save for garnish.
With vegetable peeler, take peel off 1/2 orange; bruise the peel with sugar in bowl.
Stir in other ingredients.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Remove peel and continue to chill.
Serve in pitcher with or without ice cubes.
Garnish with quarter slices of orange.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped up onion; drain grease.
Add cans and let simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Good and hearty!

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine chocolate and coffee in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until the chocolate melts.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Stir well until butter melts.
Cool.

title: mexicali chicken soup
directions: In a 4-quart pot, brown onion, chicken and cumin; pepper to taste.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings (about 1 cup each).
Soup can be made ahead.
Freezes well.

title: old-fashioned chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or until pie tests done.
Yield: 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, salt, add cinnamon.
Mix with first ingredients.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Don't grease or flour pan.

title: hushpuppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and onion.
Gradually beat in milk or water and egg.
Allow to sit 5 minutes.
Drop from a spoon into hot fat where fish was fried.
Fry until golden brown; drain on absorbent paper.
Makes about 20 hushpuppies.

title: lavone's pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice. Add sugar and Tabasco sauce. Enjoy!

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour, then stir in chicken broth.
Cook, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add all remaining ingredients except the chips.
Arrange 1/2 of chips on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add chicken mixture and top with remaining chips. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: texas torte
directions: To beaten eggs, add flour, salt and milk.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot.
Freezes well.

title: chicken breasts in parmesan cheese
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Dip each chicken breast in melted butter and coat each side with Parmesan mixture. Place coated chicken breasts on lightly greased baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.

title: lemon broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin slices of lemon, squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from remaining lemon.
Set aside.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: In a 13x9 glass casserole dish whisk the eggs and flour together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in cottage cheese and thawed broccoli.
Using a spoon "poke" the Velveeta and margarine cubes throughout the egg mixture.

title: sopaipillas(fry cakes)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Add yeast mixture and milk, mix well.
(Dough will be sticky).
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead 15 to 20 times.

title: jiffy banana pudding
directions: Combine vanilla pudding with milk, let stand until stiff, stir in Cool Whip.
In bowl, layer wafers, bananas and mixture.
Any fruit can be substituted for bananas.

title: polish chop suey
directions: Cut up roast into cubes.
Brown meat very well in frying pan. Put meat in bottom of Nesco roasting pan.
Layer with 1 package of cooked noodles and sauerkraut.
Then mix dry onion soup with water in same frying pan you browned meat
and add 1 cup mushroom soup mix.
Mix well.
Pour over all in Nesco.
Bake in Nesco for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Watch.
Nesco temperature is 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Spray bottom of 3 quart sauce pan with cooking spray.
Cook onions over medium heat until tender.
Add bacon, water and potatoes.
Simmer for 15-20 minutes until potatoes are fork tender.
With potato masher or large fork mash some of the cooked potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.

title: quick soft lemon drop cookies
directions: Combine all cookie ingredients, except Bisquick.
Beat at medium with electric mixer for 1 minute.
Add Bisquick.
Stir by hand 1 minute or until dough is of biscuit consistency.
Drop by tablespoon on lightly greased and floured cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450° for 10 minutes. Turn oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients. Place in pie pan and bake for 45 minutes.

title: "dad's" lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar. Press into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan, building up 1/2-inch edges.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake until no indentations remain when touched lightly in the center, about 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Dust with sifted powdered sugar.
Yields 25 squares.
Enjoy!

title: icebox cake
directions: Roll graham crackers fine; put all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Press into well-greased dish and chill.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: oyster stew
directions: *You might want to add even more milk to taste.

title: mexican garbage
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain grease.
Add taco mix and let simmer approximately 5 minutes.
In a separate pan, heat refried beans with 1/4 can of water.
Stir often.
Put chips on plate.
Spoon beans on chips, then hamburger.
Sprinkle on some cheese and top with sour cream.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: no name cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well; shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: celery au gratin
directions: Simmer celery in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Celery should be firm, not soft.
Drain.
Saute almonds in melted margarine. Mix with soup in saucepan and heat until bubbles form.
Stir in 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Add celery and almonds.
Pour into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Add pimentos to taste.
Bake for 20 minutes in oven that has been preheated to 325°.

title: honey apple crisp
directions: Spread sliced apples in a 1 1/2 quart heat-resistant glass utility dish.
Sprinkle with white sugar and lemon juice; pour honey all over.
Mix flour, brown sugar and salt in a bowl.
Work in butter as for biscuits, making a crumb like mixture.
Spread flour mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or crust is browned.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream and dash of cinnamon.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Wash apples.
Put in kettle with 2 cups water.
Heat to boiling.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix sugar, brown sugar and cornstarch in bowl.
Then pour over filling and stir.
Mix flour and Crisco together, then with milk.
Roll out thin.
Cut in small strips and place over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: alabama chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken; cool and pick off bones. Peel potatoes, onions and carrots. Cut in pieces and put in boiling broth from chicken. Put in chicken, beans, tomatoes, salt, pepper and vinegar. Cook for about 1 hour. Add corn and continue cooking over medium to low heat until thickened. Stir often. Serves 24.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in water until tender.
Add bouillon and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
Return to saucepan.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cheese and simmer until melted.
Serves 4.

title: congealed ambrosia salad
directions: Peel oranges, cut into bit-size pieces and set aside.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add 3 cups sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each. Alternately add flour and milk.
Add coconut.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in a tube pan.

title: play dough(do not eat!)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
May add any color food coloring. Store in airtight bags.
Have fun!

title: spinach dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheezy spinach
directions: Cook spinach as directions ask; drain well.
Spread on bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Place mushrooms over and sprinkle with pepper and marjoram.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cover with yogurt and cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix flour, salt and cayenne pepper in bowl.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add cheese, cereal and sesame seed; mix well. Shape by tablespoons into balls.
Flatten with fork on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack. Serve warm or cool.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While cake is still hot, spread Marshmallow Creme over it in pan.
Let cool, then frost with icing.

title: bread & butter pickles
directions: Soak 7 lb. medium sliced cucumbers in 3 gallon jar with 2 gallons cold water and 2 c. lime for 24 hours.
Drain and wash well.
Soak in fresh cold water for 3 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Press spinach to remove all juice.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Serve with rye bread.

title: barbecue pot roast
directions: Place chuck roast in pan and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake for 3 hours at 325°.
Pour off juices.
Pour sauce over meat. Bake 1/2 hour more.
Serve with cooked rice.
The sauce is very good spooned over rice.

title: shish kebabs
directions: In a bowl, stir together first 6 ingredients to make marinade. Place steak cubes in a large, shallow pan.
Pour marinade over steak. Stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours. Stir occasionally.
Fill 12 long skewers.
Skewer meat and vegetables, beginning and ending with meat.
Broil or grill for a total of 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.
Brush with marinade while cooking. Oil long skewers.

title: children's lemonade
directions: Pour water into clear glass.
Add sugar or honey; stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and ice cube; stir well and enjoy.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: In a bowl, coat rhubarb pieces with sugar; set aside.
In a large bowl, stir remaining ingredients together; mix well.
Stir in coated rhubarb pieces.
Turn mixture into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Serve cold, plain or with whipped cream.

title: blackberry raspberry jelly
directions: Pour juice in pan.
Add Sure-Jell.
Stir over high heat until juice boils.
Add sugar and Jell-O.
Bring to a hard rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour into jars.
Cool before serving.

title: roy's favorite chiapino
directions: Heat olive oil in Dutch oven or large kettle; saute garlic, parsley, celery and green pepper until browned.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, paprika, red wine and basil.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: mama strozier's apple nut cake
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 350° in tube pan.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding good.
Add pineapple and juice.
Add nuts, marshmallows and cherries.
Let set until firm.

title: fruit bars or cake
directions: Blend flour, spices and soda.
Set aside.
Cream butter or margarine.
Add sugar and continue blending.
Then add eggs and continue beating.
Add chopped cherries and cherry juice, alternating with dry ingredients.
Add dates and pecans.
Pour into greased Bundt pan or greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°; for a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake 30 to 45 minutes.
For Bundt pan, bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test; done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased 12 x 9-inch baking dish. Blend soup with broth; pour over chicken.
Arrange sliced eggs over chicken.
Combine flour, buttermilk and melted butter; mix well.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until crust rises to top and is golden brown.

title: wedding punch
directions: Serves 75.
Mix in a large container and add an ice ring with fruit.

title: corny onion shortcake
directions: In skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender. Remove from heat and set aside.
In bowl, combine muffin mix, egg, milk and corn.
Spread into a greased 9-inch pan. Combine sour cream, salt and 1/2 Cheddar cheese and spread over batter.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares; serve warm.

title: pecan pie(use with cream cheese crust)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla in bowl. Blend well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until set, covering outer edges of crust with foil to prevent over browning, if necessary. Bake at 350° in 9-inch pie pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Stir all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart size baking dish. Spread ketchup on top.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cut dates into small pieces into medium size bowl.
Pour hot coffee over them. Stir in sugar and butter.
Cool to room temperature. Stir in beaten egg and walnuts.
Sift flour, soda and salt onto waxed paper.
Stir quickly into date mixture just until blended. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 15 minutes. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool 5 minutes; turn out on wire rack. Cool completely.

title: almond fruit loaf - bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Butter and flour a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Combine fruit, nuts, flour, baking powder and 3/4 cup sugar; stir to mix evenly.
Use a mixer to beat eggs and 1/4 cup sugar until tripled in volume.
Pour into fruit mixture and stir with a spoon to blend.
Pack evenly into prepared pan and bake 2 hours or until done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Invert and cool on rack.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, add canned milk, add Junket and vanilla. Mix well.
Add fruit or cookies (6 large bananas, 8 to 10 peaches, 1 row Oreo cookies).
Put into canister.
Add milk to line on canister.
Make as usual for homemade ice cream.

title: greek salad
directions: Cut salad according to size needed.
Crumble Feta cheese and layer on top.
Add Greek dressing (found at Kroger).

title: tortellini soup
directions: In stockpot, put in 5 cups of water.
Bring to a boil and add bouillon cubes (see package directions).
Turn down heat to medium.
Add pureed tomatoes, tomato sauce, spices, carrots, celery and onion.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir mixture to keep from sticking.
Add finely chopped pepper and tortellini.
Cook until pasta becomes tender.
Turn heat down to simmer and continue to simmer for about 10 minutes so soup thickens.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt
butter
with
cocoa
and add sugar and eggs. Beat well. Add flour, nuts, vanilla and salt. Beat together.
Pour into greased
and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to	40
minutes.
While
cake
is
still hot spread on Marshmallow Creme and chopped pecans.

title: crab and shrimp supreme(yields six servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute veggies in butter for 3 to 4 minutes; blend in shrimp, crab and flour with veggies.
Add salt and wine.
Blend together Ricotta and sour cream, then add to crab mixture.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: nutty baklava
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cut phyllo in half crosswise and cut each half to fit pan.
Discard trimmings. Cover phyllo with a slightly damp towel.
Layer 10 sheets of phyllo in pan, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Combine nuts, coconut, brown sugar and allspice.
Mix well.
Repeat procedure twice, ending with buttered phyllo.
Cut into diamond shapes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool completely. Combine 1 cup sugar, water and honey.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Drizzle over baklava.
Cover.
Let stand 24 hours at room temperature.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes.
Mix mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in glass container for 24 hours, covered. Mix ingredients. Place in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Use 1/4 cup of remainder of liquid and 1 1/2 cups sifted powdered sugar for glaze.

title: quick cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, baking powder, salt, milk and egg.
Pour into greased 9 x 7-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter. Melt butter and pour over the top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Generously butter a Bundt pan or tube pan.
Place rolls around bottom of pan.
Cover with dry pudding, then pecans. Combine brown sugar and melted butter.
Pour butter mixture over all.
Let rise for 6 to 8 hours.
Then bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and invert on plate.
Serve warm.

title: super-spud casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in one large casserole dish or two small ones.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cook bacon.
Remove from pan.
Flour beef and brown in bacon drippings.
When browned, remove excess fat and add all ingredients to the pot.
Cover, bake 2 1/2 hours in a preheated 350 degree oven.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: oatmeal-chocolate morsel cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: thirst quencher
directions: Mix together in a glass and add plenty of ice cubes.
If diabetic, this counts as 1 fruit exchange.

title: sandra's coconut date nut balls
directions: Combine dates, oleo, sugar and eggs in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly cooked (about 10 minutes).
Set aside to cool.
When cool, add cereal and nuts. Mix and shape into balls and roll in the coconut.
Keep a bowl of cold water to wet fingers in so that mixture does not stick to hands.
Yield:
3 to 4 dozen.

title: lemon sponge cake
directions: Pour ingredients into buttered baking dish and cook in pan of water at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cake will be brown on top and custard on bottom.

title: a great do-it-now casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, add onion and green pepper.

title: snick-snacks(microwave)
directions: Combine cereals, pretzels and peanuts in 3-quart glass casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients in glass measuring cup. Heat butter mixture in microwave on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.

title: biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions together and drain.
Add tomato sauce, spices and water; simmer.
Put 5 biscuits in casserole and top with half of the meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with the other biscuits and finish with the rest of the meat and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: catriece's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour and baking soda. Set aside. In a large bowl, combine melted butter and brown sugar. Mix well. Stir in egg and vanilla until well blended. Add flour mixture and stir until just combined. Stir in chocolate chips. For each cookie, drop 1/4 cup of dough onto a cookie sheet, leaving about 2 1/2-inches between each one. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges harden and center is still soft.

title: deep-dish pizza casserole
directions: Cook meat in a medium nonstick skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring until it crumbles. Drain and return to skillet. Add tomato sauce and cook until heated.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar until well blended.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix until all is well combined.
Stir in cereal and chocolate chips.
Drop spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemonade poke cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake as directed on package for 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in pan.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour on top of nuts.
Soften cream cheese and butter with powdered sugar.
Pour on top of cake.
Press down slightly with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix instant pudding with 2 cups of juice that was reserved from the peaches and pineapple, and add fruit.
Grapes are a nice addition.
If adding bananas, do so just before serving.

title: cheesy broccoli and bacon toss
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese and onion in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice in small bowl.
Add to salad; mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Add bacon at serving time; toss to mix well.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Dredge with flour.
Brown in oil until golden on all sides.
Drain off oil.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and wine or water; cover and simmer slowly for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes a superb meal when served with hot Italian garlic bread and tossed salad.

title: meatball bites
directions: Combine meat, onions and garlic powder.
Form into bite size balls.
Heat remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Drop meatballs into liquid.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with sauce in chafing dish.

title: bran banana muffins(individualized recipe)
directions: Stir to mix.
Pour into small, paper-lined muffin tins.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 2 muffins.

title: pumpkin pie filling
directions: Combine ingredients.
Beat 2 egg yolks and whites separately. Add egg yolks and fold in egg whites.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell (unbaked).
Bake 10 minutes at 400° and then 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Whip the cream; blend with sour cream, lemon juice, sugar, salt and pineapple flavoring.
Fold in crushed pineapple, cherries, nuts and bananas.
Spoon into muffin tins which have been lined with paper cups.
Freeze until firm.
They can then be placed in large plastic bag to store in freezer.
Makes 12 to 14 individual salads.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and fluffy, then fold in other ingredients until mixed well.
Place in greased pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake at 425° until done.

title: cleo's health bread
directions: In a small bowl, proof yeast by mixing with 1/2 cup warm water and sugar.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix together the second amount of warm water, honey, molasses, oil, eggs, and lemon juice. Mix well.
Add yeast mixture and stir.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix oleo in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat egg whites to a soft peak.
Add sugar and salt; beat until very stiff.
Fold in pecans with wooden spoon.
Spread into melted oleo and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Remove to wax paper. When cool, break into pieces.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Baste on chicken.
This makes enough for about 3 chickens.
Can be frozen.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Soften cream cheese. Unroll rolls; put on cookie sheet. Pinch seams. Bake at 350° until lightly brown. Cool. Mix cream cheese, mayo and dry dressing. Spread mixture onto baked crust.
Layer ingredients that remain in order. Chill until ready to serve. Cut into squares.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Bring to boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Stir. Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well.
Pour into pan sprayed with Pam.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: holiday recipe
directions: Mix happiness, love, caring, joyful living, thoughtful insight and selfless giving all together.
Toss in a little flair. Serve to everyone you know topped with a timely prayer.

title: mexican-style tacos
directions: For authentic Mexican style tacos, try this.
Instead of ground beef, use steak - cut thin and then cut into bite-sized pieces. Saute onion in oil in a pan (don't use much onion - just enough to taste).
Add bite-sized steak pieces and cook until done.
Sprinkle with just a little bit of black pepper.
Serve on corn or flour tortillas with shredded cheese and just a few slices of jalapeno pepper.
For authentic Mexican tacos, use Chihuahua Gran cheese, or Queso Asado which should be available in the hispanic section of the grocery store.
If that is not available, use Monterey Jack cheese.
(Authentic Mexican-style tacos are not usually served with lettuce or tomato on them.)

title: banana-wine cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter to consistency of mayonnaise.
Add sugar gradually while continuing to cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and sift together.

title: meatball vegetable bake
directions: Thoroughly combine meat, egg, bread crumbs, milk, soup mix and pepper.
Shape into 8 to 10 meatballs.
Brown lightly in hot oil in skillet.
Remove meatballs and drain off excess fat; add tomatoes.
Blend water, flour and gravy base.
Stir into tomatoes. Cook until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Place meatballs in casserole; add vegetables.
Pour thickened mixture over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: barley, corn, red pepper and green onion  pilaf
directions: Heat oil in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add chopped bell pepper and half of the green onions; saute until tender, about 5 minutes. Add barley and stir to coat with olive oil. Add barley and stir to coat with olive oil.
Add broth and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally, for about 40 minutes. Add corn and stir until heated through, about 5 minutes.
Mix in sliced basil and remaining green onions. Season to taste with salt and pepper; serve.
A great dish to serve with fish or poultry. Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan sandies cookies
directions: Mix butter, 2 1/2 cups powdered sugar, vanilla and water.
Add flour; mix.
Add pecans last.
Roll in balls (rounded teaspoonfuls).
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes and turn in 1/2 to 1 pound powdered sugar.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: cherry-n-pineapple dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, combine pie filling, pineapple and lemon juice.
In medium bowl, cut margarine into cake mix until crumbly; add pecans.
Sprinkle evenly over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream if desired.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn and put in a brown paper sack.
Mix sugar, syrup and oleo.
Microwave to boil 2 - 3 minutes.
Add salt and baking soda.
Stir over popcorn in paper bag and shake well.
Place in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes take out and shake well.
Place back in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes take out and shake well this one more time.
Let cook and eat.

title: low-fat hungarian green bean salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Simply combine everything and chill at least 2 hours.
This is so simple, it's hard to believe it's so good.
Wonderful first course, or salad to go with meat or chicken dinner.
Or vegetarian dinner, too!

title: wienie surprise
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients into a casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain well.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Cut whole tomatoes into chunks.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 1/2 cups of water, then the rice.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix all chopped ingredients.
Add salt, vinegar and sugar. Simmer 5 minutes.
Can in sterilized jars.
Process 5 minutes.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Mix together cake batter and butter; set aside 2/3 cup and press the rest into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice apples and press over crumbs in pan.
Mix egg and sour cream; spread over apple layer.
Mix remaining crumbs, brown sugar and cinnamon; spread over cream layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: no-crust apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg.
Add next 2 ingredients, blend well.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool 10 minutes.

title: tortilla bake
directions: Stir together first 8 ingredients.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour some sauce mixture in bottom of 12x7x2 inch dish to barely cover.
Pour about 1/4 c. sauce in the middle of each tortilla, roll up and place in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Cover, bake until hot and bubbly in preheated 350 oven.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring water and vinegar to a boil.
Add salt and alum; bring to a boil again.
Keep liquid hot to pour over pickles.
Add 1/2 twig and 2 or 3 pieces of dill stalk and 1 garlic clove in bottom of each jar.
Pack cucumbers tightly in jar and pour hot liquid over to 1/2-inch from top. Add another 1/2 twig dill and garlic clove on top; seal jars.
Store in cool place.
Ready to eat in 30 days.

title: microwave chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt almond bark and both packages of chocolate chips in microwave.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool and set.
Makes huge batch.
Excellent for Christmas candy gifts!

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix shrimp, mushrooms, celery, onions, green pepper, hard-boiled eggs, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix bread crumbs, margarine and almonds and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: In medium pot, combine sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in water. Mix until smooth. Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and clear. Quickly stir in egg yolks. Bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in 1/3 cup lemon juice, salt and butter. Cool several hours or overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream, 1 cup cheese and sausage in casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend oil and eggs in bowl.
Mix together in separate bowl the sugar, flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Blend dry ingredients into oil and eggs.
Mix nuts in last.
Stir in diced apples.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle butterscotch bits over top; bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: no peek mystery stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan with tight fitting lid (a heavy Dutch oven).
Cover first with foil, the put tight fitting lid over foil.
Cook 3 hours at 300°.
Don't peek while cooking. Serve over buttered noodles or rice.

title: south of the border rice
directions: Brown meat, onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Add tomato sauce, picante sauce and bouillon.
While that simmers, start rice. Bring meat mixture to boil.
When rice is done, serve meat mixture over rice.
Serve with tortilla chips and refried beans.

title: orange crush pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with drink.
Add flavoring and food coloring.
Pour into pound cake pan that is already floured and greased.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cake cool completely before adding topping.

title: cabbage sausage supper
directions: In a Dutch oven or soup kettle, cook sausage and onion over medium heat until sausage is lightly browned and onion is tender; drain.
Add the cabbage and water.
Cover and cook on low for 10 minutes.
Stir in the carrots and potatoes.
Cover and cook for 25 to 30 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Serves 12.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange coffee cake(with canned biscuits)
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a small bowl.
Place about 1 teaspoon cream cheese on half of biscuit and fold over.
Press edges to seal.
Dip in melted margarine and then in sugar mixture. Place curved side down in lightly greased Bundt pan.
Drizzle remaining margarine and sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Immediately invert onto plate.

title: wine cooler
directions: Add orange juice or pineapple juice for variation.
Mix together; chill.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: mrs. prather's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: nalesniki
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar, salt and flour well and stir quickly into the eggs.
Add milk and beat hard so batter is smooth with no lumps.
Have ready 1 or 2 (6-inch) frying pans, lightly buttered and well heated.
Pour just enough batter into each to cover bottom of pan when it is tilted and swirled.
Shake the pan over the burner until they are brown on bottom and firm to touch on top.
Do not turn.
Set each aside to cool.
These can be prepared several hours before using.
Makes 16 to 18 pancakes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into thin slices (about 4 cups).
Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until tender with potatoes. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil and stir 1 minute.
Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cheese sauce on potatoes. Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 375° or until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in 9 x 12-inch pan, greased. Top with buttered bread crumbs or chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Boil noodles. Mix meat, noodles, cream of mushroom soup and tomato soup in casserole dish. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, milk and cream cheese in large mixing bowl on low speed. Add powdered sugar and whipped topping; mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top.
Store in freezer.

title: white mountain cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: strings jerky
directions: Cut away all fat, gristle and tendons from meat.
Combine seasoning in a salt shaker.
Cut red meat in 1 x 2 x 8-inch pieces and pound meat.
As you pound, sprinkle on seasoning (use about 1/2 teaspoon of seasoning on each piece).
Insert toothpick and let meat hang down through the oven rack.
Set at 150° and cook for about 7 hours.
Should feel like leather, but supple enough to bend.

title: pauper's cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt margarine in bowl.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together in a bowl.
Coat bottom and sides of a pie pan with Pam or other cooking spray.
Dip biscuits, one at a time, through margarine, then through the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place in pan, overlapping the ends of the biscuits.
Cook for 13 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 10 cinnamon rolls.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix egg, sugar, butter, flour, baking powder and pineapple juice.
Smear butter in a 12-inch cast-iron skillet.
Sprinkle and lightly pat brown sugar in the skillet.
Place pineapple slices or chunks in skillet.
Pour batter in skillet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Place a plate or serving platter upside down on top of the skillet.
Flip over.

title: chess squares
directions: Pour over crumb mixture and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook hamburger, but do not brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Break up hamburger into small pieces and place in a large pot with vegetables and seasonings.
Mix well and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: party mix
directions: Heat margarine, garlic salt, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce in a saucepan.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 250°
for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: dill dip(great with veggies!)
directions: Mix well.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: secret cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Mix the margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Heat to a boil, then pour over flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, soda, sour cream, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Five minutes before cake is done, begin making frosting in the same pan used to cook the margarine, cocoa and water.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Just mix it all together and enjoy.

title: grape ice
directions: Combine sugar and water. Heat to boiling and boil for 5 minutes. Cool. Add fruit juices. Freeze.

title: cuban sandwich
directions: Cut bread into quarters, about a foot long each.
Slice open lengthwise and place ham, pork and salami in layers along one-half of the sliced loaf.
Spread Swiss cheese along length of sandwich and add pickle slices.
Add lettuce and tomato slices.
Spread both sides of loaf with mustard and mayonnaise to taste, and close sandwich.
Warm for a minute or two to toast the outside of the bread nice and toasty.
This is easily done on a grill with a lid.

title: watergate salad
directions: Dissolve dry pistachio instant pudding with 1 can crushed pineapple.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter crispies
directions: In a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine the sugar and corn syrup.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Remember to be careful around hot steam when the lid or plastic wrap is removed.
Microwave on 100% power for 4 minutes.
Stir and scrape sides every minute, re-covering the dish each time.
While mixture is cooking, lightly grease or spray 8 x 12-inch glass dish.
Set aside.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat together cream cheese, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/4 cup sugar, then fold in 1/2 of 8 ounce container Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Using the 3 1/2 cups cold milk, prepare the 2 packages of pudding mix.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with vegetables. Yields 2 cups.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix tuna in a bowl.
Cut up onion.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Cut up boiled eggs and 1/2 cup of sweet pickle salad cubes.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain macaroni.
Chill.
Add olives and macaroni and cheese to the tuna.

title: pepper steak
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour over steak.
Bake for 1 hour or until tender in 325° oven.
Serve over rice or potatoes.

title: ham spread
directions: Mix together.
Serve on crackers or cocktail bread.

title: baked spiced fruit
directions: Drain fruit, reserving syrup for other uses.
Cut apricot, peach and pear halves in half.
Combine fruit in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine orange juice and remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool. Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Remove cinnamon stick and whole cloves before serving.
May be served hot or cold.

title: summer punch
directions: Add 7-Up or diet 7-Up to frozen concentrates as directed on cans.
Combine with apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Chill. Makes about 3 quarts.
(Soda is used in place of water.)

title: butternut squash and corn casserole
directions: Quarter squash.
Remove seeds.
In microwave-safe dish (1 1/2 quarts) place squash and 2 tablespoons water.
Cook on High 10 minutes or until tender, mash.
Microwave onion, green pepper and butter.
Stir in mashed squash, corn, crackers, cheese and optional pimento and nuts.
Cook 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Serves 5 to 6.

title: easy chocolate delight
directions: Mix pudding with milk; add Cool Whip.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers (not broken).
Pour pudding over crackers. Place another layer of crackers on pudding.
Spread frosting over crackers.
Chill 2 hours.

title: doug's stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain off excess grease.
Add garlic and Manwich sauce.
Mix well.
Add rice; mix and spoon in pepper shells.
Place peppers in small baking pan.
Add enough water to cover bottom to keep from burning pepper bottoms.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; add cheese if desired and return to oven to melt. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 6 minutes, stirring slowly.
Add vanilla and peanuts.
Drop with spoon on wax paper. Let dry.
Then store in container.

title: grits casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Let stand after taking from refrigerator for a few minutes before putting in oven.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, covered.
Serves 6.

title: cider-spiced cranberry sauce(no sugar)
directions: Combine ingredients, except optional sweetener, in a heavy saucepan.
Simmer uncovered until all berries have popped open. Cool.
Add low-calorie sweetener to taste.
Store in refrigerator. Makes about 3 cups.
Under 20 calories per tablespoon.

title: crisp pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, celery and pickle spice. Heat until sugar melts.
Put two slices of onions in each jar. Fill with cucumber chunks.
Pour syrup over to fill jar.
Seal jar and process to a rolling boil.
This makes very crisp good pickles.

title: la~vaughn's cheese ball
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and make into 2 balls. Roll balls in pecans.

title: low-fat pasta alfredo
directions: In a blender or food processor, process cottage cheese, milk and garlic until smooth.
Add flour, lemon juice, basil, mustard, pepper and salt, if desired; process until well blended.
Pour into a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Do not boil.
Serve over noodles; sprinkle with chopped tomatoes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: mum's molasses cake
directions: Cream together ingredients
in	order
given: molasses, sugar, shortening, flour,	eggs,
cinnamon,
ginger
and salt. Mix soda in boiling hot
water
before
adding to creamed mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool and use whipped cream for topping.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook carrots, onions and thyme in butter until vegetables are tender, stirring often.

title: 7-up layer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Grease and flour pans well (3 layers or large oblong).
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs smooth.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, corn meal and butter.
Place chopped pecans in unbaked pie shell and pour mixture over them.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well blended.
Press into buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Melt chips over hot water, stirring until well blended.
Spread over mixture.
Cut into squares.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Put ham in roasting pan with enough water to cover 1/4 of ham. Add vinegar.
Bake in 300° oven about 8 to 10 hours, adding more water if needed.
Cool; pull meat into pieces, discarding all fat. Discard all fat from liquid.
Using some liquid, mix with your favorite barbecue sauce, covering all meat.
May be frozen in small portions for future use.

title: mexican shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a loaf pan, spread and layer ingredients in the following order: rice, corn, onion and peppers, ground beef, tomato soup and bacon strips.
Bake for 45 minutes or until ground beef is cooked through.
Feeds 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: In medium pan, heat butter and sugar until butter is melted. Stir in flour until blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk. Add eggs and baking powder; mix well.
Add corn.
Turn into buttered casserole; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: turkey chili
directions: Heat large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add turkey and white part of scallions.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes until turkey is no longer pink, breaking up clumps with a spoon.
Stir in tomatoes, lima beans, corn and water.
Simmer 15 to 17 minutes to develop flavor.
Sprinkle with sliced scallion greens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hawaiian malt
directions: Place ingredients in blender; blend until thick.
Makes 1 serving.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until almost tender.
Beat the eggs and add to above.
Add the salt and Italian seasoning.
Cover until firm.
Can be put in a 350° oven at this point.
Cook for 25 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn and noodles(swedish dish from great-grandmother)
directions: Boil corn until tender; salt to taste.
Drain, cool and cut off cob.
Add oleo.
Add sweet milk to make liquid.
Bring to a boil.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Use 1 cup of the flour to flour fruit and nuts.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add soda to buttermilk and beat well.
Alternate flour to butter-sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Add floured fruit and nuts.
Bake 2 hours in buttered and floured tube pan at 250°.
Let cool in pan (it falls apart if you don't let it cool in pan).

title: beer bread
directions: Stir all
ingredients
together until well mixed.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: tomato-clam cocktail
directions: Mix all except the lemon peel and pepper very well.
Chill until very cold.
Give it another stir before you pour it into 8 small glasses.
Fix a twist of peel to the edge of each glass and shake a bit of pepper on top of each.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Saut bacon and onion until brown. Add frozen okra and tomatoes. Cook over low heat until okra is tender. Season with salt and pepper.

title: chicken in baggie
directions: Place fryer pieces in large Baggie.
Slice potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Add to chicken in Baggie.
Add oil, just to coat all pieces evenly.
Season with garlic.
Add paprika.
Shake well then pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until crispy and golden brown.

title: easy cheese squares
directions: Pat 1 package crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan, making sure to seal seams. Combine cream cheese, egg yolk, vanilla, lemon juice and sugar. Spread mixture over bottom crust. Top with second package of rolls; pinch seams together to form top crust. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: squash and corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute slivered pepper until soft. Add flour and stir until well blended with the butter.
Beat egg and milk together.
Combine with pepper-flour mixture and add sugar, salt and mace.
Fold in corn and drained, mashed squash. Turn into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put in layers as listed and cover.
Put in refrigerator overnight or for a couple of hours.
Stir 3/4 to 1 hour before serving.
Serves about 20 people.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers together and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers (crushed) over top and then pour 1 stick melted margarine over the crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream-style corn
directions: Add corn and 1 cup water, salt and pepper to grease.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer.
Thoroughly mix flour with cold water.
Pour into corn; simmer 3 or 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Add pineapple, fruit cocktail and chopped nuts.
Turn into graham cracker crusts.
Makes 2 pies.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs until foamy and light.
In large bowl, use electric mixer. Beat in sugar, flavoring and butter until creamy.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts at low speed.
(Mixture will be stiff.)
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into bars. Makes two dozen.

title: kiss pudding
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Add vanilla and vinegar and beat until very stiff.
Bake in 2 round cake pans which have been greased, and oiled paper added.
Bake 25 minutes at 300°.
Let cool a short time, then remove from pans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hazel everett's see's fudge recipe
directions: Melt butter or margarine and chocolate chips over double boiler and set aside.
In bowl, measure, then sift powdered sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Pour melted chips and butter over mixture and beat with beater until it turns dull.
Add chopped nuts. Spread in greased 9 x 12 pan.
Pan will be full.
Refrigerate.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together and roll out on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350°
for about 6 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease and add rest of ingredients. Cook on medium heat for 2 hours or longer.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain artichokes, reserving liquid; set aside.
Cook onion in reserved liquid in skillet until tender.
Combine eggs, bread crumbs, oregano, salt, pepper and hot sauce in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Add onion, artichokes, garlic and cheese; stir well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set.
Cut into squares to serve. Yields 4 dozen appetizer servings.

title: oysterettes
directions: Mix oil and dressing in large bowl.
Add oyster crackers and stir until liquid is absorbed.
Spread crackers on cookie sheet to dry.

title: chili enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix 1 can chili, 2 tablespoons of the onion and 1 cup of the cheese; set aside.
Stir baking mix and water to a soft dough.
Gently smooth dough into a ball on floured cloth covered board.
Knead 5 times.

title: a to z bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs and add oil and sugar; beat well.
Add your choice of A to Z, plus vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.
(For fresh pumpkin, use pumpkin pie spice instead of cinnamon.)

title: hedy's herb curry dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix 1 cup of flour and walnuts together.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Mix the eggs in one at a time.
Add the vanilla flavoring.
Add 2 cups of flour alternately with the milk.
Add the cup of flour with the nuts to the other ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: lasagna with spaghetti(quick and easy)
directions: Boil spaghetti noodles until done (7 to 9 minutes).
Drain. Layer Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheeses over noodles.
Top with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let cool for 5 minutes before you cut it.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: baked grits
directions: Cook grits in water until done, following package directions. Remove from burner and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Wonderful for holiday meals.
