title: southern cornbread
directions: In a medium sized bowl mix cornmeal, flour, egg, sugar, salt, pepper, corn and onion. Add enough milk to make a pancake-like batter. Pour mixture into a greased baking pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top starts to brown slightly. Remove from oven and slice into squares. Serve hot with butter.

title: barbara's chicken supreme
directions: Optional: Breasts can be wrapped in bacon.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 2 oiled baking pans at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Make 3 cups liquid with the 4 beef cubes and add to cooked onions.
Add seasonings and ladle into individual bowls.

title: pork tenderloin piquant
directions: This marinade is excellent for boneless pork loin as well.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; add other ingredients except pecans. Roll in pecans.

title: no bakes
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Boil for exactly 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and drop onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar or glaze.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring salt, vinegar, water, and sugar to a boil.
Pack cucumbers in jar.
Add 3 or 4 cloves of garlic to each jar.
You may add to suit your taste or may use onions instead of garlic. Add 2 to 4 heads of dill to each jar (add to suit taste). Pour hot liquid mixture over cucumbers in jar.
To seal, place jars in canner of hot water and bring to simmer; do not boil.
Turn off head and let stand in hot water for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients, then spread in greased pan (8 x 8-inch). Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Take from oven and cut into squares. These are good hot or cold. May be frozen.

title: fruit bars
directions: Arrange pecan halves in greased 8-inch square baking pan. Combine flour, egg, brown sugar and melted butter in bowl; mix well.
Pour into prepared baking pan.
Press candied fruit lightly into batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
25 servings.

title: hawaiian cheese ball
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Roll in nuts.

title: easy dessert
directions: First, melt butter or margarine
in
x
13-inch pan. Stir in flour, brown sugar,
coconut
and
pecans.
Mix
well until crumbly.
Bake at 350° in
oven for 25 minutes, stirring often. Cool.
Remove half of mix
and
set aside for topping. Spread remainder evenly over bottom
of pan.
Then mix instant pudding and milk for about 2
minutes.
Fold
in
the
whipped topping or Cool Whip.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with remaining mix. Refrigerate.

title: clam casino
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with small rye bread rounds or Ritz crackers.
Also may be used to stuff quahaugs.

title: chicken and noodles(serves 12)
directions: Mix
soups
and chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and chicken and simmer on low temperature.

title: banana bread
directions: Butter loaf pan or spray with any fat free spray (Pam, etc.) Preheat oven to 350°.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in bananas and nuts.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating only until blended.
Turn into pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; turn out of pan to cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hot asparagus rolls
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales with a vegetable peeler.
Arrange half of asparagus in a steamer basket. Place over boiling water.
Cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from steamer and place in a single layer on paper towels to cool.
Repeat procedure.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Gradually add first 4 ingredients to cream cheese and mix well.
Add shrimp and mix again.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Make crust with crescent rolls pressed into jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: coconut cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Makes 3 layers. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in double boiler and mix in brown sugar.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon in Ziploc bag. Grease Bundt pan.
Take tube of biscuits and cut each biscuit into quarters.
Put biscuits in bag of cinnamon and sugar and shake to coat evenly.
Put in Bundt pan.
Put 1/3 of brown sugar/margarine mixture on top of biscuits.
Add nuts if desired.
Repeat the procedure with each of the other tubes of biscuits.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn onto plate immediately.

title: carol's oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry on a hot griddle; turn when edges begin to firm.

title: tourtiere(french pork pie)
directions: In large kettle, cook pork, beef and onions until beef and pork are grey color.
Simmer meat over medium-low heat until fat starts coming to top, about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
If meat appears dry, add some water.
Skim fat while meat is simmering. Add spices, salt and pepper; continue simmering while the potatoes are cooking in another pot.
Drain potatoes and mash.
Add potatoes to meat mixture and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.
(If more spices are desired, add at this time.)

title: chicken marsala
directions: Place 1 piece of chicken, boned side up, between 2 pieces of clear plastic wrap.
Pound with a meat mallet to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Repeat with remaining breasts.
Spray a large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat skillet over medium heat. Add 2 chicken breasts.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, or until no pink remains.
Transfer to a platter.
Repeat with remaining breasts.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; chill well.
Serve with your favorite raw vegetables.
Yield:
2 cups dip.

title: doughnuts
directions: Combine flour, sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add lemon juice and baking soda to milk, then mix with other ingredients.
Fry at 360° to 375° in a deep fryer for 1 minute.

title: chocolate snappers
directions: Combine and beat until creamy the sugar, shortening and egg. Stir in corn syrup and Nestle Choco-Bake.
Sift together and blend in gradually remaining ingredients.
Shape into balls (size of walnuts) and roll each in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on center rack of oven.
Let stand for a few minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Bake 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: cheesy chicken spaghetti
directions: Place hen in a Dutch oven. Add water to cover. Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Remove hen, reserving 6 cups broth.
Let hen cool slightly.
Bone hen.
Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Set meat aside.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: pina colada wedges
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and rum flavoring until smooth. Fold in 2 cups of the whipped topping, pineapple with syrup and 2 cups of coconut.
Spread in 8-inch container or pan.
Freeze until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into wedges.
Garnish with pineapple and cherries, if desired.

title: horseradish green beans
directions: Cook beans with onion and bacon 30 minutes; drain well, discarding bacon.
Place into a mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients; spoon over beans, mixing well. Refrigerate at least 2 hours to allow flavors to blend.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together, adding pudding last. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Toast pecans in salt and margarine in 275° oven for 15 minutes. In small saucepan, combine sugar, water, cinnamon and salt. Cook until soft ball forms when dropped in cold water. Add vanilla, stirring well. Add half pecans and stir gently. Place nuts separately on buttered dish or wax paper. Repeat until all nuts are coated.

title: venison marinade(for venison roasts)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place venison roast in a nonmetal bowl or pan and cover with marinade.
Refrigerate overnight.
When roasting, use water in pan to enhance the flavor.

title: clam dip
directions: Soften cheese (I use a little mayonnaise and some of the clam juice for desired consistency).
Add clams and onions. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove and let it be almost at room temperature.
Serve with crackers.
(I prefer Sociables or Ritz.)

title: summer garden sauce
directions: In medium size saucepan, simmer oil and onion until golden. Add tomatoes, peppers, salt, pepper and basil.
Stir well.
Cook for 30 minutes over low heat.
Add 2 tablespoons water if sauce is too thick.
Pour over your favorite cooked pasta.
(Thin pasta is best.)
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: carrot bars with cream cheese frosting
directions: Frost bars while warm with frosting.

title: maine baked fish
directions: Mix all in a blender or food processor.
Then cook in double boiler until smooth and cheese is melted.
Pour over 1 pound haddock fillets and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger meat and diced onion; drain off fat.
Add tomato soup (do not add water).
Break up American cheese over top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
When sauce starts to bubble, stir in the cheese.
In a separate pan, bring water to boil.
Add egg noodles; cook until tender.
Drain and pour noodles into meat sauce; mix together.

title: microwave clam chowder
directions: Place butter and onions alone for 2 minutes on High.
Cook covered.
Add potatoes; cook on High 5 minutes.
Add clams with juice and can of water.
Cook for 6 to 7 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day cook in microwave to 160°, then add half and half (8 ounces).
Eat and enjoy.

title: halloween spiders
directions: Melt the chocolate chips in the microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Allow to stand and cool.
Stir.
Add corn flakes.
Stir. Drop on wax paper in tablespoons.
Add pretzels for legs.
Chill flat for 30 minutes.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, oatmeal, sugar and baking soda.
Stir in raisins (or nuts) until well coated with dry mixture.
Combine vanilla, oil, egg and milk.
Stir banana and cinnamon into liquid mixture.
Gradually combine the dry mixture with the liquid mixture until moistened.
Grease muffin tin with shortening.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 large or 9 regular muffins.

title: cake without frosting
directions: What to do:
Put the cake mix into the big bowl.
Now crack the eggs into the big bowl.
Now, put 1 1/2 cups of water into the big bowl.
Now mix well with mixer and put in the pan.
Put it in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Brown ground meat in margarine.
Add onion soup mix.
Mix water and chili sauce and vinegar.
Add pork and beans and kidney beans.
Mix well and add water, if dry.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black angel dessert(servings:  4)
directions: Melt chocolate, sugar and water in double boiler.
Stir egg yolks in gradually.
Beat well.
Let cool to room temperature. Beat egg whites.
Add half of beaten egg whites to chocolate mixture; blend.
Fold in remaining whites.
Whip heavy cream. Fold into chocolate mixture.
Tear angel food cake into bite-size pieces.
Grease a loaf pan and fill by alternating layers of cake pieces and chocolate.
Top with chocolate.
Chill 24 hours.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Brown roast and place in a deep roaster or crock-pot.
Add soups and cover meat.
Cook for 4 hours in a 325° oven or set crock-pot on high.
The meat will be fork-tender and will make a rich and natural gravy.
Serve on buns like hamburger.

title: bourbon dogs
directions: Cook overnight on low in crock-pot.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper in butter until tender. Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar, chili powder, curry powder, bay leaves and shrimp; simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and serve.

title: spinach mold
directions: Assemble ingredients in order listed. Chill. Looks weird, tastes great!!

title: venison roast supreme(serves 6)
directions: Place roast in large baking pan.
Add water, wine and bouillon cubes.
Pour mushroom soup over roast and add onion soup mix on top.
Add vegetables to water, sprinkle with spices and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and roast at 325° for 2 1/2 hours. Slice roast and cover with gravy mixture from pan, and serve.

title: cream puffs
directions: Sift flour, measure, add salt and sugar and sift again.
In saucepan combine shortening and boiling water over low heat until butter is melted.
Add flour, all at one time.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball and leaves the side of the pan.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Continue beating until thick dough is formed.
Grease 14 large muffin tin cups.
Spoon dough evenly into cups.
Round top of dough.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and then at 325° for 25 minutes or until beads of moisture no longer appear on surface.
Do not open oven door during early part of baking.
When cool, cut a slit 1/2 way between top and bottom and fill.

title: french fried onions
directions: Peel onions.
Cut in thin slices, separating the rings.
Make batter of the flour, milk, egg and salt.
Have frying pan of fat ready.
It should be just hot enough to brown a cube of bread in one minute.
Dip in onion rings, a few at a time, and fry for a few minutes.

title: quick and lite cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, mix together first three ingredients until well blended.
Add 2 eggs; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: california cole slaw
directions: Combine the cabbage with the celery, cucumber, green pepper, onions and parsley.
You may do this ahead; cover and chill.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Make stiff enough to roll and cut.
Fry in boiling lard.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix ingredients and press into large cake pan.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and grate.
Salt cucumbers and squeeze out the juice after 15 minutes.
Mix with mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.

title: crme brulee(yield: 4 six-ounce servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 325°.

title: date nut balls
directions: Measure margarine, dates, cherries and sugar into medium size saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture becomes a paste.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and pecans. Mix thoroughly.
Use tablespoon portions on wax paper.
Shape into balls.
Let stand until cool.

title: crunchy bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing and sugar in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry out bacon until nearly done.
Save a little bacon grease to add on top of beans last.
Fry out hamburger meat.
Drain grease.
Mix all other ingredients.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Cut into cubes; mix with vegetables, soup and mushrooms.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Place mixture in a casserole dish.
Mix Bisquick and milk together in a small bowl; pour on top of chicken and vegetable mixture, smoothing to cover.
Bake at 375° until topping is done and golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Sift the dry ingredients; add 1/2 to creamed mixture.
Add mincemeat; stir until blended.
Add nuts and remaining flour mixture.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Pound chicken with mallet.
Roll with bacon and close with toothpicks.
Place rolls in crock-pot.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Put on top of chicken.
Cook low for about 10 to 12 hours.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Mix egg yolks and milk. Add to sugar and cornstarch mixture.
Cook slowly over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour into casserole. Sprinkle crushed crackers surface and top with melted margarine. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: dutch oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Put all ingredients in Dutch oven or covered casserole.
Stir until well mixed.
Cover and bake for 4 hours.
Do not disturb until the 4 hours are up.
Serves 8.

title: beefy tortilla pie
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions; drain and add seasonings.
Add all the cans, undrained.
Heat and garnish with sour cream, shredded cheese and taco chips as desired.

title: pineapple-cranberry punch
directions: Combine pineapple
juice,
cranberry
juice cocktail and ginger ale in a
large bowl.
Stir in lemon juice.	Float lemon slices on top.
Yield: 25 (4 ounce) servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into small pieces and melt.
In a separate bowl, mash up the tomatoes and add the chili; mash up the beans a little.
Add to melted cheese and heat until hot.

title: canned spaghetti sauce
directions: Use equal parts of soy sauce, Italian dressing and water. Marinate any red meat for 3 or more hours before cooking.

title: chocolate raspberry whip
directions: With a mixer, combine juice concentrate, milk and Cool Whip. Pour into a graham cracker pie shell and allow to sit 2 hours in the freezer before serving.
Filling is also good served chilled in glasses.
May be served with regular Cool Whip as garnish.

title: homemade stickers
directions: Bring vinegar to a boil; add gelatin.
Reduce heat to low. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add extract.
Makes 1/2 cup glue.
While warm, brush on the back of stickers-to-be such as wrapping paper, magazine papers, greeting cards, etc.
Let dry. Trim, lick and stick.
Leftover glue will keep for many months in an airtight container.
Just heat before reusing.

title: fruity whip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Pour milk into small mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 1 minute.
Set bowl of gelatin in larger bowl of ice and water.
Stir until slightly thickened, then whip with electric mixer until fluffy, thick and doubled in volume.
Blend pudding into whipped gelatin.
Pour into serving bowl or individual dishes.
Chill until set.
Serve with spoonful of regular or lite Cool Whip.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: raspberry congealed salad
directions: Drain blueberries and pineapple and add water to make 1 cup liquid.
Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water and 1 cup liquid. Fold in fruit.
Congeal.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons of oil until soft.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil and ground beef.
Cook slowly until lightly browned, using Dutch oven.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, enchilada sauce mix, water and beans.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Slice cucumbers thinly.
Put cucumbers in large bowl.
Add flour, corn meal, salt and pepper.
Stir until all cucumbers are coated.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Mix well all together.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: baked butter chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Melt stick of better in baking pan in oven.
Cut up chicken and season with salt and pepper (or other desired seasoning).
Flour chicken just as you would to fry. Remove the pan from the oven when the butter is completely melted. Roll chicken in butter to coat and place in pan to bake.
Bake uncovered for about an hour, or until golden brown.

title: hamburger casserole(variation)
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cut up potatoes and cook in enough water (about 1 cup or less).
Add all ingredients to hamburger and simmer for 3 or 4 hours.
Can use crock-pot, if desired.

title: banana cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour 2 round baking pans.
In a mixer bowl combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add shortening and banana; beat on low speed of electric mixer until combined.
Add buttermilk or sour milk, eggs, and vanilla; beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Turn batter into prepared pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes on wire racks.
Remove from pans; cool thoroughly.
Frost with creamy butter frosting.

title: southern-style ribs
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring frequently. Baste ribs with sauce and smoke 1/2 hour on each side.
Baste again.
Wrap in foil.
Smoke for 2 hours.
Turn and baste; cover with foil.
Smoke 1 hour.
Unwrap, baste and smoke 1/2 hour on each side or until done.

title: salsa sauce
directions: Drain tomatoes of all liquid before mixing with other ingredients.
Mix and cook on medium heat.
Stir often.
(May stick to bottom of pan.)
Cook for 1 hour or more.
Cook until thick. Makes 8 pints.

title: northwest cheesecake supreme
directions: Combine the crumbs, 3 tablespoons of sugar and butter.
Press onto a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: mama's chocolate cake
directions: In a 2-quart pan, bring to a boil oleo, 4 tablespoons cocoa, Crisco and water.
Mix together the dry ingredients.
Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in glass pan or for a brownie-like thin cake, bake in a cookie sheet.

title: myrtle's pudding
directions: Mix pudding until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In cake pan, layer bottom with crackers (whole).
Pour half of pudding mixture on top of crackers.
Put another layer of crackers.
Pour rest of pudding on crackers.
Lay another layer of crackers, then spread chocolate icing.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: bran muffins by the pailful
directions: Combine bran and salt.
Stir in boiling water.
Let set for 1 minute.
Add milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Cream in sugar and shortening to bran mixture.
Beat in eggs and dry ingredients.

title: zippy apples
directions: Mix apples with a few tablespoons of brown sugar, cinnamon, cloves and a couple tablespoons of honey. Mix in dried fruit bits. Place in greased dish. Pour over orange juice. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until apples are softened.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; blend until crumbly.
Spread over apples. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rosy apple pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, water and cinnamon candies; cook until candies dissolve.
Pare, core and slice apples; add to sugar mixture.
Simmer until apples are red. Drain; save syrup.
Blend flour into cooled syrup and add lemon juice.
Spread apples in a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate.
Pour syrup over apples.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust; seal and flute edges.
Cut slits for escape of steam.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until desired brownness.

title: cranberry candle salad(this is an edible centerpiece!)
directions: Heat cranberry sauce, strain, set berries aside.
Dissolve Jell-o in hot juice and water.
Add salt and lemon juice.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Place 1/2 package of onion soup in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Place rice over it.
Cover with mixture of mushroom soup and water.
Lay chicken on top and sprinkle with the other 1/2 package of onion soup.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: waffles
directions: Just mix together.
Add blueberries if you like for variety.

title: orange freeze smoothie
directions: Wash strawberries; remove and discard greens.
Peel banana. Freeze strawberries and banana.
Juice oranges; blend orange juice with frozen fruits on medium speed for 1 minute.
Serve.

title: microwave party mix
directions: Melt margarine and add seasonings.
In a large Ziploc plastic bag place cereals, nuts and pretzels.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal.
Zip up and shake until cereal is coated.
Pour into a long glass dish to fit your microwave and cook on High for about 6 minutes. Stir every 2 minutes.
Spread on paper towel.
When cool, store in covered container.

title: country bean soup
directions: Rinse beans and cover with 8 cups water and boil, covered, for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand for 1 hour.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: hot cocoa
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and salt. Blend in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil. Remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Beat with rotary beater or whisk until foamy.
Serve with choice of options. Serves 5 (8 ounce servings).

title: orange salad
directions: Toss lettuce, onion, celery, oranges and almonds together in large bowl. In a mixing bowl whisk together remaining ingredients. Pour over lettuce mixture and serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry onion and hamburger until brown; drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 8.

title: tart-riffic delights
directions: Combine instant pudding and cold milk in a mixing bowl according to package directions.
On a plate, set out approximately two cups of any fresh fruits you wish to use.

Pick fruits with different colors to make the tarts more attractive. Using a spoon, fill each tart half-way full with the pudding. Arrange fruit on top of the pudding in an attractive pattern. Measure out 1/4 cup of apple jelly and put it into a small saucepan.
Place the saucepan on the stove and melt the apple jelly over low heat for 15 minutes or until melted.
Stir occasionally.
Using a pastry brush, spread the apple jelly over the fruit tarts for a pretty glaze.
Chill for at least one hour before serving.

title: spring lamb roast
directions: Do not wash leg of lamb, but rub well with a cloth dipped in vinegar.
Salt and pepper the lamb; fry in hot fat on all sides. Add minced onion.
Roast in medium oven at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, basting frequently.
Shortly before end of roasting time, mix sugar, ginger and cloves; put on roast.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add dressing to taste.
Serve with Doritos.

title: macaroni and frank casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
Set aside.
Melt oleo in large saucepan over low heat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add flour.
Stir well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Pour Kahlua over cooled brownies after you have poked holes in them.
In large serving bowl, layer 1/2 brownies, 1/2 Skor bars, 1/2 mousse and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers until all are used up.

title: sausage noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown sausage.
Drain both.
While noodles drain, mix the mushroom soup, milk and cheese, allowing to simmer. Put sausage mixture and noodles into greased casserole dish. Cover with foil.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: "my grandmother's boiled raisin cake"
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased loaf pans and bake in 300° oven for about 1 3/4 hours.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put all dry ingredients in one bowl.
Blend sugar and oil in another bowl.
Then add beaten eggs and pumpkin to the sugar and oil mixture.
Then slowly add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and mix.
Put in 2 loaf pans (well-greased).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Feel free to add walnuts or raisins.

title: nannan's easy shrimp creole
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add onion and cook slightly.
Add biscuit mix and stir until well blended.
Combine remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice.
Add with onion mixture to crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 4.9 hours.
One hour before serving, turn on high setting and add shrimp.
Remove bay leaf and serve over hot fluffy rice.
Provides 6 servings, about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Dip 3 tortillas in enchilada sauce.
Place in bottom of greased flat pan.
Add 1/4 meat mixture, 1/4 cheese and 1/4 soup. Continue layers.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce over top.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Blend butter and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla and water. Add flour and nuts.
Chill 1 hour in refrigerator.
Form into small roll about size of finger or round balls.
Place on cookie sheet close together.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: smoky cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Chill slightly.
Shape into ball.
Coat with 1 cup finely chopped nuts (pecans or almonds).
Serve with crackers.

title: redfish macadamia
directions: Mix together milk and eggs on shallow bowl and set aside. Pulverize nuts.
Add flour, pepper, garlic salt and parsley.
Dip fish fillets in milk-egg mixture, then roll in flour mixture.
Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown.
Serve with lemon.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Cook rice (omit butter).
Cool, add onions, peppers and olives.
Combine marinade, curry and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add rice and artichoke.
Garnish with lettuce.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: easy rhubarb jam
directions: Combine fruits with sugar.
Stir over low heat until sugar is melted.
Cook over medium heat 10 to 12 minutes until clear and thick.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin.
Seal at once.

title: israeli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill until ready to serve.

title: strawberry, cream cheese and pretzel dessert
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and pretzels and mix.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until fluffy; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on crust, then refrigerate.
Make jello with boiling water, then add frozen strawberries.
Let set for 30 minutes; stir and spread on top of cream cheese mix.
Refrigerate overnight or until jello is set.

title: quick dessert(from eater's choice)
directions: Pour undrained pineapple into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over the top. Sprinkle nuts over the cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: grandma's rivel soup
directions: Heat milk to boiling point.
Add salt.
To make rivels, rub egg and flour together, then add half and half.
These are best made by cutting through mixture with 2 forks.
When rivels are about the size of cherry stones, drop into hot milk.
Keep milk at boiling point for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until soft; mash well, then add sugar, melted butter, 2 well beaten eggs, vanilla and milk.
Pour in casserole, then add topping.

title: peas and macaroni
directions: Saute onions in a little oil. When soft, add frozen peas and some water. While cooking, make your macaroni. When macaroni is al dente (not mushy), combine the peas and serve with grated Romano cheese.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together. Cut in shortening. Make a well in center of dry ingredients and pour in buttermilk. With a fork, stir lightly until all particles are moist.
Pour onto floured pastry board and work in flour until dough isn't sticky. Pat or roll out dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in a greased pan and bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with melted butter.
It makes a crisp, flaky biscuit.
Makes about 15 biscuits.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Brown the bacon and onion; remove from heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and put into an uncovered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chips.
Pour over Chex.
Add confectioners sugar.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine candy bars and 1/2 cup butter over low heat until candy bars are melted.
Stir constantly, then cool.
Cream sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine buttermilk and soda and add to cream mixture and flour, then stir in candy mixture and pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for one hour.
Top with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: philippine rice
directions: Brown pepper, carrot and onion in oil. They will brighten when done. Set aside. Brown ground beef, saving drippings. Combine rice and pepper mixture with beef and drippings. Add salt and pepper. Mix well and add soy sauce, stirring over heat. May add celery if desired.

title: bacon, broccoli, chicken pasta
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Separate and fry to a crisp in a large skillet.
Remove bacon to a paper towel.
Leave bacon grease.
Add olive oil and crushed garlic.	Cook until garlic is light brown.
Add broccoli and stir-fry.
Cook spaghetti according to box directions.	After draining, mix small amounts of spaghetti, bacon, chicken and broccoli with grease back to the stockpot and mix well.
Serve hot and top with Parmesan cheese. Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: new hampshire squash casserole
directions: Butter inside of casserole.
Mix all ingredients well, except nuts.
Pour mixture into casserole.
Sprinkle with the chopped walnuts or pecans.
(I use more over top.) Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: pineapple dressing for fruit salad
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Blend in pineapple juice and orange juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Slowly stir mixture into beaten eggs.
Return to saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Beat into cream cheese.
Chill.
Yields 2 cups.

title: todd's marinade(for pork or beef)
directions: Mix and pour over meat at least one hour before cooking.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: Cook ditalini or other pasta as directed on package. Heat olive oil in a large saucepan. Add onion, celery, carrot and garlic. Cover and cook 6 minutes or until tender. Add dry white wine and boil 1 minute. Stir in beans, chicken broth, tomato sauce, basil and oregano. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes to develop flavors. Add drained pasta; mix to coat. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: honey cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together well.
Add honey, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time. Chill.
Roll in balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 6 dozen.
Add crushed nuts to batter, if preferred.

title: mud hens
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add 3 egg yolks and 1 white and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and beat in butter mixture until blended.
Pour into 9 x 14-inch pan which has been lightly greased and floured.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Beat last 2 egg whites and gradually add brown sugar.
When stiff, spread over batter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
In small ovenproof bowl, alternate layers of crumbs and oysters.
Pour soup over top; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
With a spoon, level top.
Bake meat loaf 1 1/2 hours.
Let set 1/2 hour before serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Sift together flour, salt, sugar and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Beat smooth.
Adjust batter thickness with additional milk or flour.
Heat oil in 8-inch skillet.
Heat oil to 360°.
Cover bottom of funnel with finger. Pour in 1/2 cup of batter and release into hot oil in spiral movement.
Fry golden about 3 minutes.
Turn carefully.
Cook 1 minute more, then drain on paper.
Sprinkle with sugar or serve with syrup.
They are best hot!
Microwave leftovers.

title: stir and drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Stir in oil and vanilla and blend in sugar.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt in another bowl.
Add to sugar mixture and refrigerate.
After chilling, preheat oven to 400°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet (3 in a row).
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately with spatula.

title: sucket(candied citrus peel)
directions: Remove peel from oranges and put in saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes. Drain, rinse, cover with cold water and boil for 15 more minutes. Drain.
Remove white membranes by gently scraping with spoon.
Cut into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Combine 3 cups water, sugar and spices.
Boil until sugar dissolves.
Add peel and cook until syrup is absorbed.
Drain.
Remove spices.
Toss peel in sugar until it is coated.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: In saucepan beat egg slightly.
Stir in milk, sugar and margarine.
Cook and stir over medium heat, about 12 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread on cake.
Frost top of 13 x 9-inch cake or two 8 or 9-inch cake layers.

title: chocolate town special cake
directions: *To sour milk, use 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon vinegar plus milk to equal 1 1/3 cups.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Chop butter into cake mix.
Pat into 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Peel and thinly slice apples.
Arrange on top of cake.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over the apple slices

title: layered bean dip
directions: Layer bean dip in pie plate. Pour jar of picante sauce on top. smooth sour cream on top and add cheese, jal., and olives.

title: pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt, stirring well.
Add shortening, cutting it in with a fork, until a coarse mixture results.
Add cold water.
Shape into a ball.
Roll out into 8-inch round. Place in pie pan.

title: lemon meringue squares
directions: Press on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple cobbler rolls
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat sugar and water in saucepan until sugar melts.
Mix lard and flour.
Add milk and stir until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto floured board and knead
just until smooth.
Roll out into a large rectangle 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples and then sprinkle apples over dough.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Wet edges of dough with a little water and seal.
Slice dough into 1/2-inch pieces and place in melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup over rolls and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook until thick and pour hot over fruit of your choice.

title: krazy kake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pudding, together and bake in an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 28 to 30 minutes.
Top with pudding when served.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt margarine.
Add peanut butter and powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered plate and cool.
Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: frozen cherry salad loaf
directions: Drain fruit. Soften cream cheese and beat until fluffy. Blend in sour cream, sugar and salt. Fold in fruit, marshmallows and pecans. Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and freeze overnight. Slice. Yield: 8 servings.

title: chex party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Heat margarine.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
In roaster, add Chex, pretzels and nuts.
Pour mixture of margarine, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce on top.
With a wooden spoon, stir well.
Heat for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: amber cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar; mix thoroughly. Spread mix into lightly greased 10 x 15 x 1/2-inch pan and bake for 45 minutes at 275°.
Remove from oven.
Use a teaspoon to scoop out cookies.
Form into balls with fingers.
It's hot.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. Excellent with ham or pour over block of cream cheese and spread on crackers.
Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.	Yield:	3 cups.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Cook celery and carrot in boiling water until tender.
Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour.
Add milk and chicken broth; cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir to blend.
Stir in vegetables and water.
Serve topped with chopped parsley.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil, club soda, nuts and pudding. Beat well.
Bake at 350° until done, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and butter.
I melt butter in an iron skillet and pour into mixture.
Then bake in iron skillet at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mustard, in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and clears.
Add a few drops of water to dry mustard to make a paste. Pour sauce into individual dishes and drop a dollop of hot mustard into each.
Serve with egg rolls.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add salt and butter to the water.
When boiling, add flour all at once, stirring constantly, until mixture leaves sides of pan. Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating constantly. Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered pan, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, make a cut in top and fill.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Boil spaghetti noodles as package indicates.
Melt butter in microwave-safe dish or on top of stove.
Add can of shrimp (and juice, if you like a stronger flavor; if not, use canned chicken broth or water).
Add spaghetti noodles.
Add package of Ranch dressing to mixture.
Add Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add juice from oranges.
Fold in whipping cream and orange sections.
